@ \chapter{Boot sequence}

Drol uses a custom Broderbund boot chain, not DOS 3.3. The disk is not
DOS-formatted and has no catalog. The entire boot sequence is:

\begin{enumerate}
\item The Disk II controller PROM (P5A) reads Track 0, Sector 0 to [[$0800]]
   and jumps to [[$0801]]. This is the standard Apple II boot process (``boot0'').
\item Boot1 at [[$0801]] loads 10 more sectors from Track 0 to [[$5000--$59FF]]
   using the PROM's re-entry point at [[$Cn5C]].
\item Boot1 copies the Apple II ROM to language card RAM, relocates the
   loader and RWTS code, and jumps to the loader.
\item The loader reads the game data from subsequent tracks into memory
   and launches the game.
\end{enumerate}

\section{Disk layout}

The P5A PROM reads sectors in the order they physically appear on the disk
as it rotates. Due to the 16-sector format's physical interleave, the
sectors pass under the head in this order:

\begin{center}
\begin{tabular}{cccccccccccccccc}
0 & 7 & E & 6 & D & 5 & C & 4 & B & 3 & A & 2 & 9 & 1 & 8 & F \\
\end{tabular}
\end{center}

The [[.dsk]] file format stores sectors by sector number (0--F).
To find the file offset of the Nth sector read by the PROM:

\begin{verbatim}
    POSITION_ORDER = [0, 7, E, 6, D, 5, C, 4, B, 3, A, 2, 9, 1, 8, F]
    sector_number  = POSITION_ORDER[N]
    file_offset    = track * 4096 + sector_number * 256
\end{verbatim}

\section{Track 0 memory map}

Boot0 reads Sector 0 to [[$0800]] (boot1 code). Boot1 then reads the next
10 sectors to [[$5000--$59FF]]:

\begin{center}
\ra{1.3}
\begin{tabular}{cccl}
\toprule
\thead{Position} & \thead{Sector} & \thead{Memory} & \thead{Contents} \\
\midrule
0 & 0 & [[$0800]] & Boot1 \\
1 & 7 & [[$5000]] & RWTS: sector read entry, address field reader, data field reader \\
2 & E & [[$5100]] & Loader subroutines: drive select, delay, seek, read track, init \\  % TODO-SYM: $5100
3 & 6 & [[$5200]] & Seek routine continued, nibble constants \\
4 & D & [[$5300]] & Read buffer (zeros at boot, filled during sector reads) \\
5 & 5 & [[$5400]] & Page destination table (maps sectors to memory pages) \\
6 & C & [[$5500]] & Main loader dispatch \\
7 & 4 & [[$5600]] & Unused (all zeros) \\
8 & B & [[$5700]] & Zero page save area (initialized with boot-time ZP snapshot) \\
9 & 3 & [[$5800]] & RWTS high-level code (relocated to [[$BE00]]) \\
10 & A & [[$5900]] & Reset handlers and screen address table (relocated to [[$BF00]]) \\
\bottomrule
\end{tabular}
\end{center}

After loading, boot1 performs these relocations:

\begin{itemize}
\item [[$D000]]--[[$FFFF]]: Apple II ROM copied to language card RAM.  % TODO-SYM: $D000 $FFFF
\item [[$D000]]--[[$D7FF]]: Copy of [[$5000]]--[[$57FF]] (loader/RWTS under language card).  % TODO-SYM: $D000 $D7FF $57FF
\item [[$BE00]]--[[$BEFF]]: Copy of [[$5800]]--[[$58FF]] (RWTS high-level code).  % TODO-SYM: $BEFF $58FF
\item [[$BF00]]--[[$BFFF]]: Copy of [[$5900]]--[[$59FF]] (reset handlers, screen address table).  % TODO-SYM: $BFFF $59FF
\end{itemize}

The loader code thus lives in two places: at [[$5000]]--[[$57FF]] in main RAM (where  % TODO-SYM: $57FF
it executes during loading), and at [[$D000]]--[[$D7FF]] under the language card (a  % TODO-SYM: $D000 $D7FF
backup copy).

\section{Boot1}

Boot1 occupies Track 0, Sector 0 ([[$0800]]--[[$08BF]]). The first byte ([[$0800]])  % TODO-SYM: $08BF
is the sector count for boot0; the PROM reads this value and loads that many
sectors. Here it is [[$01]], meaning boot0 loads only Sector 0 itself. After
loading, boot0 sets [[$27]] = [[$09]] (the next destination page) and jumps to  % TODO-SYM: $09
[[$0801]].

@ Boot1 is the first code executed after the PROM's boot0. It operates in
three phases, re-entered at [[$0801]] by the PROM after each sector read:

\textbf{Phase 1} --- When [[$27]] = [[$09]] (immediately, since boot0 just set it):  % TODO-SYM: $09
switch to hi-res graphics mode, derive the slot number, patch the JMP
instruction for PROM re-entry, set reset vectors, and redirect
loading to [[$5000]] by setting [[$27]] = [[$50]].

\textbf{Phase 2} --- While [[$27]] $<$ [[$5A]]: jump to [[$Cn5C]] to read the next
sector. The PROM stores it at page [[$27]], increments [[$27]], and re-enters
[[$0801]]. This loads 10 sectors to [[$5000--$59FF]].

\textbf{Phase 3} --- When [[$27]] $\ge$ [[$5A]]: all sectors loaded. Copy ROM to
language card, relocate loader and RWTS, display splash text, and jump
to the loader entry at [[$51C0]].

<<boot1 defines>>=

; Zero page locations used by boot1 and the PROM.
DEST_PAGE       = $27           ; PROM: destination page for next sector read
SLOT_X16        = $2B           ; Slot number * 16 (e.g. $60 for slot 6)

; Soft switches for graphics mode.
SW_HIRES        = $C057         ; Hi-res mode
SW_PAGE1        = $C054         ; Display page 1
SW_FULLSCR      = $C052         ; Full screen (no text window)
SW_GRAPHICS     = $C050         ; Graphics mode (vs text)

; Language card soft switches.
LC_BANK1_RWROM  = $C081         ; LC bank 1: write RAM, read ROM
LC_BANK1_ROROM  = $C080         ; LC bank 1: read-only ROM (write-protect RAM)

; Reset and NMI vectors.
SOFTEV          = $03F2         ; Soft entry vector (reset handler)
SOFTEV_CHK      = $03F4         ; Checksum for SOFTEV ($03F3 EOR #$A5)
NMIVEC          = $FFFC         ; NMI vector (2 bytes, in language card)

; Monitor ROM routines.
MON_HOME        = $FC58         ; Clear screen

; Loader variables in RESET_R page.
LDR_TRACK       = $BF48         ; Current track number
LDR_SLOT        = $BF49         ; Slot number * 16
LDR_PHASE       = $BF4A         ; Boot phase counter ($FF = first boot)

; Loader entry point (in loader binary, not accessible by label).
LOADER_INIT     = $51C0         ; Loader init entry point

; Text screen.
TEXT_SCREEN      = $0400         ; First line of text screen
@

<<boot1 entry>>=

        ORG $0800
        SUBROUTINE

        ; Boot sector entry -- multi-phase loader for Drol.
        ;
        ; Inputs:
        ;   DEST_PAGE -- destination page set by boot0 PROM
        ;   X -- slot number * 16 (from PROM)
        ;
        ; Behavior:
        ;   Phase 1 (DEST_PAGE=$09): switches to hi-res graphics, patches
        ;     re-entry JMP and reset vector, redirects loading to RWTS_ENTRY.
        ;   Phase 2 (DEST_PAGE<$5A): returns to PROM to read next sector.
        ;   Phase 3 (DEST_PAGE>=$5A): copies ROM to language card, relocates
        ;     RWTS to RWTS_RELOAD, backs up loader to $D000, decodes splash text,
        ;     and jumps to loader entry.
        ;
        ; Modifies:
        ;   SOFTEV, SOFTEV_CHK, NMIVEC, LDR_SLOT, LDR_PHASE, LDR_TRACK,
        ;   RWTS_RELOAD-$BFFF (RWTS), $D000-$D7FF (loader backup), language card RAM

BOOT1_SECTORS:
        .BYTE $01               ; Sector count for boot0 (just this sector)

; --- Entry point: PROM jumps here after each sector read ---

BOOT1_ENTRY:
        LDA DEST_PAGE           ; Current destination page
        CMP #$09                ; First entry? (boot0 sets DEST_PAGE=$09)
        BNE .check_done         ; No, check if loading is complete

; --- Phase 1: first entry after boot0 ---

        BIT SW_HIRES            ; Switch to hi-res graphics mode
        BIT SW_PAGE1            ; Display page 1
        BIT SW_FULLSCR          ; Full screen (no text window)
        BIT SW_GRAPHICS         ; Graphics (not text)

        TXA                     ; X = slot * 16 (from PROM)
        LSR                     ; Shift right 4 times
        LSR                     ;   to get slot number
        LSR                     ;
        LSR                     ;
        ORA #$C0                ; Form $Cn (slot ROM page)
        STA .jmp_reentry+2      ; Patch JMP target high byte
        STA SOFTEV+1            ; Reset vector high byte = $Cn
        EOR #$A5                ; Compute checksum
        STA SOFTEV_CHK          ; Store reset vector checksum
        LDA #$00
        STA SOFTEV              ; Reset vector low byte = $00
        LDA #$5C
        STA .jmp_reentry+1      ; JMP low byte = $5C (PROM re-entry)
        LDA #$50
        STA DEST_PAGE           ; Redirect loading to RWTS_ENTRY

; --- Phase 2: continue loading, or Phase 3: done ---

.check_done:
        LDA DEST_PAGE
        CMP #$5A                ; Loaded all 10 sectors? ($5000-$59FF)
        BCS .loading_done       ; Yes, proceed to phase 3
.jmp_reentry:
        JMP $C65C               ; No, read next sector (patched to $Cn5C)

; --- Phase 3: all sectors loaded ---

.loading_done:

; Copy the entire Apple II ROM ($D000-$FFFF) to language card RAM.
; Reading $C081 twice selects LC bank 1 for writing with ROM readable.
; The LDA/STA through the same pointer reads from ROM, writes to RAM.

        LDA LC_BANK1_RWROM      ; LC bank 1: write RAM, read ROM
        LDA LC_BANK1_RWROM      ; (must read twice to enable writes)

        LDX #$30                ; $30 pages = $D000-$FFFF (48 pages)
        LDY #$00
        STY $00                 ; Pointer low = $00
        LDA #$D0
        STA $01                 ; Pointer high = $D0
.copy_rom:
        LDA ($00),Y             ; Read from ROM
        STA ($00),Y             ; Write to LC RAM
        INY
        BNE .copy_rom
        INC $01                 ; Next page
        DEX
        BNE .copy_rom

; Set NMI vector in language card to point to RESET_R (reset handler).

        LDA #$BF
        STA NMIVEC+1            ; NMI vector high = $BF
        STA SOFTEV+1            ; Reset vector high = $BF
        EOR #$A5
        STA SOFTEV_CHK          ; Reset checksum
        LDA #$00
        STA NMIVEC              ; NMI vector low = $00
        STA SOFTEV              ; Reset vector low = $00

; Copy $5800-$59FF to RWTS_RELOAD-$BFFF (RWTS and reset handlers).

        LDX #$00
.copy_rwts:
        LDA $5800,X
        STA $BE00,X
        LDA $5900,X
        STA $BF00,X
        INX
        BNE .copy_rwts

; Store slot number and initialize loader state.

        LDX SLOT_X16            ; Slot * 16 from PROM
        STX LDR_SLOT            ; Save for loader
        LDA #$FF
        STA LDR_PHASE           ; Phase = $FF (first boot, not yet started)
        LDA #$00
        STA LDR_TRACK           ; Current track = 0

; Copy $5000-$57FF to $D000-$D7FF (loader backup under language card).
; This is a self-modifying loop: the source and destination addresses
; are incremented in-place.

        LDX #$00
.copy_loader:
        LDA $5000,X             ; Source: $5000 (patched)
        STA $D000,X             ; Dest: $D000 (patched)
        INX
        BNE .copy_loader
        INC .copy_loader+2      ; Increment source page
        INC .copy_loader+5      ; Increment dest page
        LDA .copy_loader+2      ; Check source page
        CMP #$58                ; Done when source reaches $5800
        BNE .copy_loader

; Switch back to ROM (write-protect language card).

        LDA LC_BANK1_ROROM

; Clear the text screen.

        JSR MON_HOME

; XOR-decode 40 bytes from SPLASH_TEXT to the text screen.
; In this disk image the source bytes are all zero, so $0400 gets
; filled with $AB (the XOR key), which displays as "+" characters.
; On the original disk this may have been a Broderbund copyright line.

        LDX #$00
.decode_text:
        LDA SPLASH_TEXT,X
        EOR #$AB
        STA TEXT_SCREEN,X       ; First line of text screen
        INX
        CPX #$28                ; 40 columns
        BNE .decode_text

; Enter the loader.

        JMP LOADER_INIT         ; Loader init entry point

; Pad to fill the rest of the sector with zeros.
; SPLASH_TEXT-$08F7: splash text (XOR-encoded, all zeros in this image).

        DS $D0-(*-$0800),0

SPLASH_TEXT:
        DS $28,0                ; 40 bytes of encoded text (all $00)

        DS $0900-*,0            ; Pad to end of sector
@ %def BOOT1_SECTORS BOOT1_ENTRY SPLASH_TEXT

<<boot1.asm>>=
        PROCESSOR 6502
<<boot1 defines>>
<<boot1 entry>>
@

\section{Loader}

After boot1 jumps to [[$51C0]], the loader takes over. The loader occupies
[[$5000--$59FF]] (loaded from Track 0 by boot1) and manages reading game
data from subsequent tracks into memory.

The loader has two entry points:
\begin{itemize}
\item [[$5000]]: Re-entry from game code. Saves zero page to [[$5700]],
  then falls through to [[$51C0]].
\item [[$51C0]]: Entry from boot1. Restores the slot and track numbers from
  [[$BF49]]/[[$BF48]] to zero page, then jumps to the main dispatch
  at [[$5500]].
\end{itemize}

The RWTS (Read/Write Track/Sector) uses standard Apple II 16-sector nibble
encoding with D5~AA~96 (address field) and D5~AA~AD (data field) prologues.
The 6-and-2 nibble translate table lives at [[$52D6--$53D5]], spanning the
RWTS work buffers at [[$5200]] and [[$5300]].

The [[$5800]]--[[$59FF]] region is relocated by boot1 to [[$BE00]]--[[$BFFF]] and contains  % TODO-SYM: $59FF $BFFF
the high-level RWTS entry, reset handlers, screen buffer routines, and the
hi-res address lookup table. The loader itself never calls into the relocated
RWTS code; it uses its own sector reading routines at [[$5003]]--[[$50C6]]. The  % TODO-SYM: $50C6
relocated code at [[$BE00]]--[[$BFFF]] is used only by the game.  % TODO-SYM: $BFFF

\subsection{Disk layout}

The 35-track disk is organized as follows:

\begin{center}
\ra{1.3}
\begin{tabular}{cl}
\toprule
\thead{Tracks} & \thead{Contents} \\
\midrule
0      & Boot1 + loader/RWTS ([[$5000]]--[[$59FF]]) \\  % TODO-SYM: $59FF
1--4   & Persistent game code (loaded once at first boot) \\
5--9   & Level data set 0 (phase 0) \\
10--14 & Level data set 1 (phase 1) \\
15--19 & Level data set 2 (phase 2) \\
20--24 & Level data set 3 (phase 3) \\
25--34 & Unused \\
\bottomrule
\end{tabular}
\end{center}

\subsection{Memory map after first boot}

Memory is split into two categories: \textbf{persistent game code} loaded
once from tracks 1--4, and \textbf{swappable level data} loaded from a
5-track group that changes with each phase.

\begin{center}
\ra{1.3}
\begin{tabular}{lll}
\toprule
\thead{Address} & \thead{Source} & \thead{Type} \\
\midrule
[[$0100]]--[[$01EF]] & Track 1 S0--S1 $\to$ [[$5C00]], copied & Stack page init \\  % TODO-SYM: $01EF
[[$0200]]          & Track 5+ S0                          & Level data (swappable) \\
[[$0300]]--[[$03EF]] & Track 1 S0--S1 $\to$ [[$5D00]], copied & Vectors / data \\  % TODO-SYM: $03EF
[[$0400]]--[[$12FF]] & Tracks 1--2                           & Game code (persistent) \\  % TODO-SYM: $12FF
[[$1300]]--[[$18FF]] & Track 5+ S1--S6                       & Level data (swappable) \\  % TODO-SYM: $1300 $18FF
[[$1900]]--[[$1FFF]] & Track 2                               & Game code (persistent) \\  % TODO-SYM: $1900 $1FFF
[[$2000]]--[[$3FFF]] & ---                                   & Hi-res page 1 (framebuffer, not loaded) \\  % TODO-SYM: $3FFF
[[$4000]]--[[$47FF]] & Tracks 2--3                           & Game code (persistent, entry at [[$4000]]) \\  % TODO-SYM: $47FF
[[$5000]]--[[$59FF]] & Track 0                               & Loader / RWTS (persistent) \\  % TODO-SYM: $59FF
[[$5C00]]--[[$5DFF]] & Track 1 S0--S1                        & Staging buffers \\  % TODO-SYM: $5DFF
[[$5E00]]--[[$5FFF]] & Track 4 S10--S11                      & Game code (persistent) \\  % TODO-SYM: $5E00 $5FFF
[[$6000]]--[[$66FF]] & Track 3                               & Game code (persistent) \\  % TODO-SYM: $66FF
[[$6700]]--[[$72FF]] & Track 5+ S7--S15, Track 6+ S0--S2    & Level data (swappable) \\  % TODO-SYM: $6700 $72FF
[[$7300]]--[[$74FF]] & Track 3                               & Game code (persistent) \\  % TODO-SYM: $7300 $74FF
[[$7500]]--[[$7AFF]] & Track 6+ S3--S8                       & Level data (swappable) \\  % TODO-SYM: $7500 $7AFF
[[$7B00]]--[[$8BFF]] & Tracks 3--4                           & Game code (persistent) \\  % TODO-SYM: $7B00 $8BFF
[[$8C00]]--[[$BDFF]] & Tracks 6+--9+                         & Level data (swappable) \\  % TODO-SYM: $8C00 $BDFF
[[$BE00]]--[[$BFFF]] & Track 0 ([[$5800]]--[[$59FF]]), relocated   & RWTS / reset handlers \\  % TODO-SYM: $BFFF $59FF
\bottomrule
\end{tabular}
\end{center}

The game calls back to the loader via [[JMP $5000]] to swap in a new
level set. The loader cycles through phases 0--3, each reading 5
consecutive tracks (5--9, 10--14, 15--19, 20--24). Each phase replaces
75 pages (19,200 bytes) of level data while leaving the persistent
game code untouched.

<<loader defines>>=

