@ \chapter{Game initialization}

The game entry point is [[$4000]], called by the loader's [[FIRST_BOOT]]
via [[JSR $4000]]. The first 19 bytes ([[$4000]]--[[$4012]]) are NOPs --- the  % TODO-SYM: $4012
original copy protection was patched out. The real initialization begins
at [[$4013]].

\section{HUD/frame unpacker}

[[GAME_INIT]] at [[$4013]] unpacks a data stream from [[$4100]] into hi-res
page~1 ([[$2000]]--[[$3FFF]]), drawing the static HUD and playfield frame  % TODO-SYM: $3FFF
(score panels, lives/level indicators, and wall/floor borders --- \emph{not}
the DROL logo, which is drawn later). The stream consists
of 37 records, each containing a 2-byte destination address (lo/hi)
followed by 40 data bytes. A [[$FF]] terminator ends the stream.  % TODO-SYM: $FF

After [[GAME_INIT]] returns, [[FIRST_BOOT]] sets up vectors, detects
the joystick, applies machine-specific patches, restores zero page from
[[ZP_SAVE]], and enters the game via [[JMP ($004E)]]. The initial
value of [[$4E]]/[[$4F]] from [[ZP_SAVE]] is [[$72A3]], which is in the  % TODO-SYM: $4F
swappable level data area loaded from track~5.

The 37 records only touch rows 0--32 and 188--191 of hi-res page~1;
every other scanline is left in whatever state the framebuffer was in
when [[GAME_INIT]] started. Figure~\ref{fig:hud-frame} shows what
the page looks like immediately after [[GAME_INIT]] returns, assuming
a cleared framebuffer: the static score/hiscore HUD, the player-lives
and level indicators, and the purple wall/floor frame of the playfield.
The DROL logo and any other foreground content are drawn later by the
attract-mode sprite routines ([[ATTRACT_ANIM_1..4]] at [[$17A6]]/[[$17E1]]/[[$1813]]/[[$1844]])
which composite sprite pointer tables into hi-res page~2 for the
animated title sequence.

The 237 bytes immediately after the stream terminator
([[$4713]]--[[$47FF]]) are \emph{dead residue}, not a continuation of the  % TODO-SYM: $47FF
unpacker --- see [[SECTOR_RESIDUE_47XX]] below.

\begin{figure}[H]
\centering
\includegraphics[width=0.9\textwidth]{images/hud_frame.png}
\caption{Hi-res page~1 contents immediately after [[GAME_INIT]]
returns. Rendered by simulating the unpacker on
