        SUBROUTINE
        ; Broadcast A across 105 interlaced hi-res row positions at
        ; column X on page 1 ($2000-$3FFF), then RTS.  Helper called
        ; once per outer-loop iteration of CLEAR_PAGE1 (with A=$00) and
        ; per-iteration of INTERLACE_RESTORE_P1 (with A=$0300,X --- a
        ; column-indexed text-buffer byte).  The 105 STA abs,X
        ; instructions are unrolled to avoid a row-base lookup table.
        ;
        ; The painted rows form 3 contiguous playfield bands of 35
        ; rows each (rows 72-106, 112-146, 152-186), with the three
        ; text-strip boundary rows 67/107/147 and the top-HUD / bottom-
        ; text areas deliberately excluded (those are handled by
        ; CLEAR_PAGE1's inline stripe loop and text-loop respectively).
        ; Each group of 3 consecutive STA operands paints the SAME
        ; relative row in each band (row R in band 0, row R+40 in
        ; band 1, row R+80 in band 2), weaving the 3 bands together
        ; over 35 groups.  The Apple II hi-res interleaved memory map
        ; scatters these rows across the HGR1_BASE-$3FFF page at
        ; $28/$80/$400 strides; the STA operand sequence below is the
        ; hand-computed address for each row.
