\section{Rescue-child draw, collision, and projectile-spawn}

[[RESCUE_DRAW]] at [[$0C98]] is the per-frame draw + collision sibling of
[[RESCUE_UPDATE]].  It iterates the same 20-slot rescue-child
entity table (Y $\in [0, [[$13]]]$), draws each active slot's body sprite
on the playfield, and runs three independent collision/spawn checks:

\begin{enumerate}
\item \emph{Floor-enemy collision} ([[$0DAB]]--[[$0DEF]]): if the rescue  % TODO-SYM: $0DAB $0DEF
  child overlaps any of the four floor-enemy slots
  ([[ZP_ENEMY_FLAG]]/[[ZP_ENEMY_COL]]/[[ZP_ENEMY_Y]] at [[$9B]]/[[$9F]]/[[$A3]]),
  both die together: clear the enemy slot, set [[ENTITY_ACTIVE]],Y to
  drift ([[$FF]]), arm [[RESCUE_COUNTDOWN]] = [[$04]], award +[[$0035]] BCD via  % TODO-SYM: $FF
  [[SCORE_ADD]].  This is the same enemy table [[ENEMY_C_DRAW]] checks.
\item \emph{Player pickup} ([[$0DF0]]--[[$0E11]]): if the entity is in the  % TODO-SYM: $0DF0 $0E11
  centre screen-X band [[[$40]], [[$50]]) and the player row [[ZP_PLAYER_COL]]
  is within $[$entity\_row$-$[[$12]], entity\_row$+$[[$19]]$]$, set  % TODO-SYM: $12
  [[ZP_HIT_FLAG]] to [[$FF]] and merge into the same drift +  % TODO-SYM: $FF
  reward path as the floor-enemy hit.  No [[ZP_LIVES_BCD]] decrement
  --- this is the rescue, not a life-loss.
\item \emph{Hostile projectile spawn} ([[$0E13]]--[[$0E50]]): if neither  % TODO-SYM: $0E13 $0E50
  collision fired \emph{and} the entity row is odd \emph{and} the
  rescue's assigned floor [[RESCUE_FLOOR]] equals the player's current
  floor [[ZP_PLAYER_FLOOR_CUR]] \emph{and} a free projectile
  slot exists (some [[ZP_PROJ_DIR]] ([[$C5]],X) byte is zero, X $\in [0,
  [[$31]]]$), seed that slot with the rescue's direction, row, and
  screen-X --- the rescue child throws a hostile projectile picked up
  by [[HAZARD_CHECK]] on subsequent frames.  Plays a [[$0D]]-pitch
  click ([[SND_DELAY_DOWN]] with X=[[$0A]]) on emit.
\end{enumerate}

\paragraph{Per-slot dispatch.}  After [[RESCUE_DRAW_PERSPECTIVE_CACHE]]
pre-computes the player's perspective offset into [[ZP_PERSP_OFFSET_LO]] / [[ZP_PERSP_OFFSET_HI]], the body iterates Y from [[$13]]
down through the 20 slots and dispatches on [[ENTITY_ACTIVE]],Y:

\begin{itemize}
\item [[$00]] (inactive): skip to next slot.
\item +ve (active walking): compute screen-X and proceed to draw +
  collision + projectile-spawn.
\item [[$FE]] (exit-anim): skip --- the child is in its terminal  % TODO-SYM: $FE
  walk-off-screen animation and is invisible during the fade.
\item other -ve (drift): play descending click via the per-slot
  [[RESCUE_DRIFT_PITCH]] table ([[$0213]]) indexed by [[RESCUE_COUNTDOWN]],
  patch the [[SMC_SPRITE_MASK_OP]] flicker slot to [[AND
  \#imm]] for one frame so the body sprite flashes, then proceed to
  draw without running collision (the slot is invulnerable while
  drifting).
\end{itemize}

\paragraph{Sprite selection.}  The rescue child has four sprite
variants picked by walking direction ([[RESCUE_DIR]]) and step phase
([[RESCUE_ANIM]]):

\begin{center}
\begin{tabular}{l|l|l|l|l}
Phase & +dir lo/hi base & +dir h & -dir lo/hi base & -dir h \\
\hline
mid-step (anim $\notin \{0,7,8\}$) & [[$75F0]]/[[$76F0]] & [[$1C]] & [[$75E2]]/[[$76E2]] & [[$1C]] \\  % TODO-SYM: $1C
end-step (anim $\in \{0,7,8\}$)    & [[$75E9]]/[[$76E9]] & [[$1A]] & [[$75DB]]/[[$76DB]] & [[$1A]] \\
\end{tabular}
\end{center}

All four variants are width [[$03]] and indexed by [[PROJ_FRAME_IDX]]
([[$1B8F]],X) where X is the rescue's screen-X residue.  The end-step
variant additionally plays an ascending-pitch click via
[[SND_DELAY_UP]] ([[$109E]] with X=[[$0A]], A=[[$0C]]) --- the soft footstep
sound as each step completes.  The screen-column [[ZP_SPRITE_X]]
is sourced from [[PROJ_SCREEN_COL]] ([[$1C34]],X) and the row from
[[ENTITY_FLOOR_POS]],Y.

\paragraph{Drift sound.}  The drift-state click (4 frames during the
[[$04]]-step countdown after a hit) reads its pitch from
[[RESCUE_DRIFT_PITCH]] at [[$0213]] indexed by the current
[[RESCUE_COUNTDOWN]] (1..4) --- four descending-tone frames make the
``pop'' sound when the child is collected.  The flicker mask byte
loaded into [[SMC_SPRITE_MASK_ARG]] is sourced from
[[$D7,X]] (top of the entity-record block; the value is
quasi-random per frame and per slot) so each drift frame draws a
slightly different alternating pattern.

\paragraph{Common post-draw block.}  After each draw, the routine
re-loads [[ENTITY_ACTIVE]],Y at [[$0D9E]].  If still positive, runs the  % TODO-SYM: $0D9E
collision/spawn block at [[$0DAB]].  If negative (drift-mode draw just  % TODO-SYM: $0DAB
finished), restores [[SMC_SPRITE_MASK_OP]] to [[$24]] (the BIT-NOP that  % TODO-SYM: $24
disables the flicker patch) and skips collision --- drift-mode rescues
are invulnerable and cannot throw projectiles.

\paragraph{Hit-box geometry.}  The floor-enemy collision uses Y-extent
half-widths from [[$42]] / [[$43]] (level-fixed parameters loaded from  % TODO-SYM: $42 $43
[[$029A]]/[[$029B]] by [[INIT_LEVEL_STATE]]); the X-extent is a fixed 10-pixel  % TODO-SYM: $029A $029B
window (CMP enemy\_col, then SBC \#[[$0A]] and re-CMP).  The player
pickup uses the centre-band CMP \#[[$40]] / CMP \#[[$50]] X-test and a
fixed 25/18 row band around [[ZP_PLAYER_COL]].

\paragraph{Pre-compute helper [[RESCUE_DRAW_PERSPECTIVE_CACHE]].}
Sub-entry called once at the top of the routine; reads
[[PERSPECTIVE_XOFF_LO]]([[ZP_PLAYER_Y]]) - [[ZP_SPRITE_XREF]] and
[[PERSPECTIVE_XOFF_HI]]([[ZP_PLAYER_Y]]) - 0, storing the 16-bit
result into [[ZP_PERSP_OFFSET_LO]] / [[ZP_PERSP_OFFSET_HI]] ([[$0F]] /
[[$10]]).  Each per-slot inner loop then computes the rescue's
screen-X residue as
[[ENTITY_FLOOR_COL]],Y $-$ [[ZP_PERSP_OFFSET_LO]] (with high-byte
match required, so off-screen entities are clipped to the off-camera
``next slot'' branch via the [[BNE $0CAA]] guard).

\paragraph{Sprite art.}  Figure~\ref{fig:rescue_sprites} shows all
28~rescue-child body frames.  The four rows correspond to the four
animation variants from the selection table above (+dir end,
+dir mid, -dir end, -dir mid); each row has seven frames indexed by
[[PROJ_FRAME_IDX]].  All 28~sprites are [[$04]]~bytes per row
(that is, [[ZP_SPRITE_W]]~=~[[$03]]) with the end-step variants at
height~[[$1A]] and the mid-step variants at height~[[$1C]].  The pointer  % TODO-SYM: $1C
tables are inside [[drol.bin]] but the sprite bytes themselves
([[$A3C3]]--[[$AF8F]]) live in the swappable level-data region and were  % TODO-SYM: $A3C3 $AF8F
extracted from [[drol.dsk]] by replaying the loader's phase-0 track
read.

