\section{Beam subsystem: target controller}

[[BEAM_TARGET_TICK]] at [[$1230]] is the state machine for the player's
laser-beam subsystem.  Together with [[BEAM_TARGET_DRAW]] and
[[BEAM_UPDATE]] it implements a vertical beam that descends between
floors, telegraphs its target, and sprays short-lived horizontal
tracers from slots on each floor it crosses.  All three routines are
called only from [[BEAM_UPDATE]], which is itself gated on
[[ZP_PROJ_GATE]] ($32)~--- difficulty tier ``standard'' or ``maximum''
(score $\geq$~10000).

The beam is tracked by a pair of bytes on page~2:

\begin{itemize}
\item [[$03FF]]~= [[BEAM_STATE]]: [[$00]] idle, [[$0]]X active-chase, [[$8]]X
  active-attack (X~=~target floor index, 0--4).
\item [[$03FE]]~= [[BEAM_Y]]: current scanning Y-coordinate.
\end{itemize}

[[BEAM_TARGET_TICK]] advances that state machine one step:

\begin{enumerate}
\item If the sound counter [[ZP_BEAM_SND_CTR]] is non-negative,
  play the next note of the post-hit jingle from [[BEAM_JINGLE]] and decrement the counter (falls through regardless).
\item If [[BEAM_STATE]] is $<$[[$80]] but nonzero (``chase'' phase),  % TODO-SYM: $80
  decrement [[BEAM_Y]] by~2 each frame, play a pitch-[[$10]] click; on
  reaching [[$7E]],X$+1$, flip to ``attack'' phase (set bit 7).  % TODO-SYM: $7E
\item If [[BEAM_STATE]]$ \geq$[[$80]] (``attack'' phase), advance  % TODO-SYM: $80
  [[BEAM_Y]] by~2 toward [[FLOOR_Y_TABLE]]$[{\rm X}]$; on arrival,
  clear [[BEAM_STATE]].
\item Otherwise (idle), when [[ZP_BEAM_TICK]] is~0, seed a new
  target: [[BEAM_Y]]~$\leftarrow$~[[FLOOR_Y_TABLE]]$[[[$09]]]$ and  % TODO-SYM: $09
  [[BEAM_STATE]]~$\leftarrow$~[[$09]] (chase phase targeting floor~[[$09]]).  % TODO-SYM: $09
\end{enumerate}

(The exact meaning of ZP~[[$09]] is not yet pinned down; it is the  % TODO-SYM: $09
target-floor index sourced when a new beam is launched, and is used
again in [[$1297]] as the index into the per-floor thresholds.)

