\section{Beam subsystem: target draw and collision}

[[BEAM_TARGET_DRAW]] at [[$1297]] renders a short vertical sprite trail
between [[BEAM_Y]] and the current target floor's Y, then checks the
four tracked enemies for collision with that trail.

\begin{enumerate}
\item If [[BEAM_STATE]] is~[[$00]], RTS.
\item Compute $\Delta Y$~=~[[FLOOR_Y_TABLE]]$[{\rm state\_lo}]
  - $~[[BEAM_Y]].  If zero, RTS.  Clamp to 4 if $\geq$~5, otherwise
  use the raw delta as sprite height.
\item Draw the beam sprite at [[$B529]] via [[DRAW_SPRITE]], using  % TODO-SYM: $B529
  width~2, height~$\Delta Y$, column~[[$24]], Y~=~[[BEAM_Y]].  (The  % TODO-SYM: $24
  source-pointer operands at [[SMC_DS_SRC_LO]] /
  [[SMC_DS_SRC_HI]]~=~[[$65B3]]/[[$65B4]] are patched to~[[$B529]].)  % TODO-SYM: $B529
\item For each of four enemy slots X~=~3..0: if [[ZP_ENEMY_FLAG]],X
  ([[$9B]]) is zero, skip.  Otherwise fetch [[ZP_ENEMY_COL]],X ([[$9F]])
  as an index into [[PROJ_SCREEN_COL]] and require the
  screen column to be in $[[[$23]], [[$25]])$.  If so, compare  % TODO-SYM: $23 $25
  [[BEAM_Y]] against [[ZP_ENEMY_Y]],X ([[$A3]]) $\pm$~3:
  a~\emph{hit} zeros the enemy flag, clears [[BEAM_STATE]],
  re-arms the post-hit jingle ([[ZP_BEAM_SND_CTR]]~$\leftarrow$~[[$0A]]),
  and awards 100~BCD points via [[SCORE_ADD]].
\end{enumerate}

The ZP symbols [[$9B]]/[[$9F]]/[[$A3]]/[[$A7]]/[[$AB]] introduced here  % TODO-SYM: $A7
([[ZP_ENEMY_FLAG]], [[ZP_ENEMY_COL]], [[ZP_ENEMY_Y]]) are four-slot
parallel tables for enemies tracked by the beam.  These overlap the
ESC-key location at [[$9B]] (renamed here from [[KEY_ESC]] for the
purposes of this subsystem; the ESC-key alias only aliases [[$9B]] when
the input dispatcher polls it).

\paragraph{Beam sprite and ready-prompt.}  The beam source pointer
[[$B529]] is sprite id~0 of the general [[SPRITE_TABLE]] family at  % TODO-SYM: $B529
[[$B000]]/[[$B080]] (the main 128-entry sprite pointer table shared by
attract, enemy-B, and UI draws).  Adjacent id~1 at [[$B535]] is the  % TODO-SYM: $B535
``ready'' prompt sprite drawn at the top of each level intro by
[[LEVEL_INTRO_TICK]].  Both live in the swappable level-data region
and are shown in Figure~\ref{fig:sprite_table_ui} --- the beam's
sprite bytes are the first [[$0C]] bytes at [[$B529]] and render as a  % TODO-SYM: $B529
short vertical dashed trail; the ready-prompt sprite is
$[[$04]]\times[[$0F]]$ (W=[[$03]], H=[[$0F]]).

