\section{Beam subsystem: per-frame update}

[[BEAM_UPDATE]] at [[$130A]] is the main-loop entry for the player's
laser-beam subsystem.  It is called unconditionally from
[[MAIN_LOOP]] but returns immediately whenever the difficulty gate
[[ZP_PROJ_GATE]] ($32) is negative~--- i.e.\ at the minimum and
moderate tiers (see [[DIFFICULTY_UPDATE]]).  At standard or maximum
tier the gate is [[$01]] (positive), and the routine:

\begin{enumerate}
\item Ticks the beam target state machine ([[BEAM_TARGET_TICK]]).
\item Draws the beam sprite trail and checks enemy collisions
  ([[BEAM_TARGET_DRAW]]).
\item Runs the tracer-spawn scheduler ([[BEAM_TRACER_SPAWN]])~--- see
  below.
\item Walks the 5-slot tracer table from Y~=~4 down to 0
  ([[TRACER_STATE]] at~[[$0237]], [[TRACER_ROW]] at~[[$023C]]).  Each active
  slot's state byte ([[$0237]],Y) is both its remaining lifetime and,
  via the inner body, the X-coordinate where a single [[$7F]] pixel  % TODO-SYM: $7F
  byte is drawn directly into the hidden hi-res page.
\end{enumerate}

\paragraph{Per-slot animation.}  An active slot ([[TRACER_STATE]],Y
is non-negative) decrements its state byte and writes it back.  If
the new value is negative, the slot becomes inactive and the loop
moves on.  If it is [[$12]] or [[$13]] the slot is in the ``near-player''  % TODO-SYM: $12
window and a hit test fires: when the player's floor ([[ZP_PLAYER_COL]]
= [[$06]]) matches [[TRACER_ROW]],Y within a 18-column band, the player
is killed ([[ZP_HIT_FLAG]] $\leftarrow$ [[$FF]]) and the slot is  % TODO-SYM: $FF
deactivated.  Otherwise, the slot computes the screen row address
for [[TRACER_ROW]],Y using the [[SCREEN_ROW_ADDR_LO]] /
[[SCREEN_ROW_ADDR_HI]] tables (with a $+$[[$20]] high-byte adjust when
[[ZP_PAGE_FLAG]] is negative, targeting hi-res page~2) and stores the
constant byte [[$7F]] at screen[row][col~=~new state].  The HUD/playfield  % TODO-SYM: $7F
bounds are enforced by comparing the column against
[[HUD_LIVES_COL]] and [[HUD_SCORE_COL]]: the
draw is suppressed whenever the column would overlap the HUD.
(These column bounds are seeded by [[GAME_START_INIT]] and updated
by the HUD layout code at [[$6200]] as the lives count changes.)  % TODO-SYM: $6200

[[BEAM_TRACER_SPAWN]] at [[$1376]] scans the same five slots for the
first inactive one.  On every other frame ([[ZP_FRAME_COUNTER]] bit 0
set), when the beam is chasing ([[BEAM_STATE]] nonzero) and the
current [[BEAM_Y]] is strictly less than the per-level threshold
[[FLOOR_THRESH]]$[{\rm state\_lo}]$ ([[$83]]), the found slot is
activated: its [[TRACER_ROW]] $\leftarrow$ [[BEAM_Y]] and its
[[TRACER_STATE]] $\leftarrow$ [[$22]] (initial lifetime~=~34).  A
[[$0A]]-pitch/[[$0A]]-duration click is played through [[SND_DELAY_UP]] to emit the spawn tick.

\paragraph{Self-modifying code.}  Two operand bytes inside the inner
animation loop are patched each iteration to hold the computed screen
row address: [[SMC_TRACER_ADDR_LO]]~=~[[$1359]] (low) and
[[SMC_TRACER_ADDR_HI]]~=~[[$135A]] (high).  They are initialised in the
on-disk image to~[[$00]]/[[$90]] respectively, so the unpatched opcode
would store into [[$9000]],X; the runtime always rewrites both bytes
before the store fires.

<<beam update defines>>=

; --- Zero-page (beam subsystem) ---
ZP_BEAM_TICK    = $F8           ; Pre-activation tick (0 triggers beam seed)
ZP_BEAM_SND_CTR = $F9           ; Post-hit jingle counter ($00..$0A, $FF=idle)
; $09 holds the target floor index when a new beam is seeded
; ($03FF = state byte low nibble after seed).

; --- Page-2 beam state (overlaid on 5-slot tracer table) ---
TRACER_STATE    = $0237         ; 5-slot lifetime / X-column ($FF = inactive)
TRACER_ROW      = $023C         ; 5-slot floor-row index (paired with state)
BEAM_JINGLE     = $0241         ; Post-hit jingle pitch table (read via ZP_BEAM_SND_CTR)
BEAM_Y          = $03FE         ; Current beam Y scan position
BEAM_STATE      = $03FF         ; Beam state: $00 idle, $0X chase, $8X attack

; --- Four-slot enemy tracking (read by BEAM_TARGET_DRAW) ---
ZP_ENEMY_FLAG   = $9B           ; 4-slot enemy active flag (aliases KEY_ESC)
ZP_ENEMY_COL    = $9F           ; 4-slot enemy column index (PROJ_SCREEN_COL,Y)
ZP_ENEMY_Y      = $A3           ; 4-slot enemy Y coordinate

; --- Per-floor parameters (read by BEAM_TRACER_SPAWN) ---
FLOOR_THRESH    = $83           ; Per-level floor threshold (Y-coord limit)

; (ZP_SCORE_ADD_LO/HI are defined in score-add defines.)

; --- Sprite-draw SMC operands (patched by BEAM_TARGET_DRAW) ---
; (SMC_DS_SRC_LO/HI for DRAW_SPRITE are SMC_DS_SRC_LO/SMC_DS_SRC_HI.)
SMC_DS_SRC_LO   = $65B3         ; DRAW_SPRITE source-ptr low operand
SMC_DS_SRC_HI   = $65B4         ; DRAW_SPRITE source-ptr high operand

; --- Sound-click wrappers ---
SND_DELAY_UP    = $109E         ; Speaker-click delay, ascending
SND_DELAY_DOWN  = $1091         ; Speaker-click delay, descending

; --- Callable routines ---
DRAW_SPRITE_B529 = $656F        ; DRAW_SPRITE (alias for the beam-draw call)
@

<<beam update>>=

        ORG $130A
BEAM_UPDATE:
        SUBROUTINE
        ; Per-frame beam subsystem: target-machine + tracer animation.
        ;
        ; Called unconditionally from MAIN_LOOP.  Returns immediately
        ; if ZP_PROJ_GATE (set by DIFFICULTY_UPDATE) is negative ---
        ; i.e.\ at the minimum and moderate difficulty tiers.
        ;
        ; Inputs:
        ;   ZP_PROJ_GATE        --- $FF = subsystem off; else on.
        ;   BEAM_STATE        --- beam target state machine.
        ;   BEAM_Y            --- current beam Y scan position.
        ;   TRACER_STATE ($0237..B)   --- 5-slot tracer lifetime/X.
        ;   TRACER_ROW ($023C..40)    --- 5-slot tracer floor-row.
        ;   ZP_PAGE_FLAG        --- select hi-res page 1 vs 2.
        ;   ZP_PLAYER_COL       --- player floor number for hit test.
        ;   ZP_FRAME_COUNTER    --- every-other-frame spawn gate.
        ;
        ; Behavior:
        ;   Three sub-handlers advance the beam state
        ;   (BEAM_TARGET_TICK), draw it and run enemy collision
        ;   (BEAM_TARGET_DRAW), and spawn tracer particles onto active
        ;   floors (BEAM_TRACER_SPAWN).  Then a 5-slot loop
        ;   decrements each tracer's state and, unless the new state
        ;   enters the $12..$13 hit window, writes a single $7F byte
        ;   into hi-res memory at the computed row/column.
        ;
        ; Modifies:
        ;   TRACER_STATE, ZP_HIT_FLAG on player hit, and the two SMC
        ;   operands SMC_TRACER_ADDR_LO/HI inside its own body.
        ; Clobbers: A, X, Y

; --- Difficulty gate ---
        LDA ZP_PROJ_GATE                ; $32: $FF when subsystem off
        BPL .active
        RTS
.active:
        JSR BEAM_TARGET_TICK            ; Advance beam state machine
        JSR BEAM_TARGET_DRAW             ; Draw beam + enemy collision
        JSR BEAM_TRACER_SPAWN            ; Spawn tracers on active floors

; --- Walk 5 tracer slots from Y=4 down to 0 ---
        LDY #$04
.next_slot:
        LDX TRACER_STATE,Y
        BPL .active_slot                ; Active if non-negative
.advance_y:
        DEY
        BPL .next_slot
        RTS

; --- Active slot: decrement lifetime / advance X ---
.active_slot:
        DEX
        TXA
        STA ZP_DRAW_LOOP_IDX            ; $5C scratch: new state value
        STA TRACER_STATE,Y
        BMI .advance_y                  ; Just retired (went from 0 to $FF)
        CMP #$13
        BEQ .hit_check                  ; Near-player hit window: $12 or $13
        CMP #$12
        BEQ .hit_check

; --- Still travelling: compute screen row + draw a $7F pixel byte ---
; Two operand bytes inside the STA at .draw_byte are rewritten each
; frame by this block: SMC_TRACER_ADDR_LO and SMC_TRACER_ADDR_HI
; hold the effective screen-row address (low, high).
.draw_pixel:
        LDX TRACER_ROW,Y                ; Floor-row index
        LDA SCREEN_ROW_ADDR_LO,X        ; row-address low byte
        DC.B $8D                        ; STA abs opcode (force 3 bytes)
        DC.W SMC_TRACER_ADDR_LO         ; Patch operand
        LDA SCREEN_ROW_ADDR_HI,X        ; row-address high byte
        BIT ZP_PAGE_FLAG                ; $00: +$20 high when page 2
        BPL .page1
        CLC
        ADC #$20
.page1:
        DC.B $8D                        ; STA abs opcode (force 3 bytes)
        DC.W SMC_TRACER_ADDR_HI         ; Patch operand
        LDX ZP_DRAW_LOOP_IDX            ; New state = screen column
        CPX HUD_LIVES_COL                ; Skip if col >= playfield right bound
        BCS .skip_draw
        CPX HUD_SCORE_COL                ; Skip if col < playfield left bound
        BCC .skip_draw
        LDA #$7F                        ; Single horizontal-line pixel byte
        DC.B $9D                        ; STA abs,X opcode (force 3 bytes)
SMC_TRACER_ADDR_LO:                     ; operand low (patched)
        DC.B $00
SMC_TRACER_ADDR_HI:                     ; operand high (patched)
        DC.B $90
.skip_draw:
        JMP .advance_y

; --- Near-edge hit test: state reached $12 or $13 ---
.hit_check:
        LDA ZP_PLAYER_COL               ; $06: player floor
        CMP TRACER_ROW,Y
        BCS .draw_pixel                 ; player_floor >= tracer_floor: safe
        CLC
        ADC #$12
        CMP TRACER_ROW,Y
        BCC .draw_pixel                 ; player_floor+18 < tracer_floor: safe
        LDA #$FF
        STA ZP_HIT_FLAG                 ; $1E: player hit
        STA TRACER_STATE,Y              ; Retire this tracer
        BMI .advance_y                  ; Always taken ($FF)

; --- Tracer spawn scheduler (called from BEAM_UPDATE) ---
BEAM_TRACER_SPAWN:
        SUBROUTINE
        ; Find an idle tracer slot and, on odd frames with an active
        ; beam whose Y is under the per-floor threshold, seed it.
        ;
        ; Inputs:
        ;   TRACER_STATE ($0237..B)   --- 5-slot state (BMI = inactive).
        ;   ZP_FRAME_COUNTER    --- AND #$01 gates spawn.
        ;   BEAM_STATE / BEAM_Y
        ;   FLOOR_THRESH ($83,X)      --- per-floor Y threshold.
        ;
        ; Behavior:
        ;   On a successful spawn, TRACER_STATE := $22 (initial lifetime
        ;   and X-column), TRACER_ROW := BEAM_Y, and a click sound is
        ;   played.
        ; Clobbers: A, X, Y

        LDY #$04
.find_inactive:
        LDA TRACER_STATE,Y
        BMI .try_spawn                  ; Found an idle slot
        DEY
        BPL .find_inactive
        RTS                             ; All slots busy: no-op

.try_spawn:
        LDA ZP_FRAME_COUNTER
        AND #$01
        BEQ .done                       ; Every other frame only
        LDA BEAM_STATE
        AND #$0F                        ; State low nibble = target floor
        TAX
        LDA BEAM_Y
        CMP FLOOR_THRESH,X              ; FLOOR_THRESH[X]: per-floor Y limit
        BCS .done
        STA TRACER_ROW,Y                ; Row := beam Y
        LDA #$22
        STA TRACER_STATE,Y              ; Lifetime := $22
        LDA #$0A
        LDX #$0A
        JSR SND_DELAY_UP                ; Spawn click
.done:
        RTS
@ %def BEAM_UPDATE BEAM_TRACER_SPAWN SMC_TRACER_ADDR_LO SMC_TRACER_ADDR_HI
@ %def TRACER_STATE TRACER_ROW BEAM_JINGLE BEAM_Y BEAM_STATE
@ %def ZP_BEAM_TICK ZP_BEAM_SND_CTR
@ %def ZP_ENEMY_FLAG ZP_ENEMY_COL ZP_ENEMY_Y FLOOR_THRESH
@ %def SMC_DS_SRC_LO SMC_DS_SRC_HI SND_DELAY_UP SND_DELAY_DOWN
@ %def DRAW_SPRITE_B529

\section{Enemy-A advance timer}

[[ENEMY_A_ADVANCE]] at [[$13D6]] is the per-frame tick for the first of
three ``moving hazard'' slots maintained in the contiguous entity
block [[$D4]]--[[$EC]] (copied from [[$029C]] by [[INIT_LEVEL_STATE]]).  The  % TODO-SYM: $EC $029C
slot's four-byte record is:

\begin{center}
\begin{tabular}{ll}
[[ZP_ENEMY_A_STATE]] & Control byte: [[$00]] inactive; positive =
                              steady tick; negative = PRNG-gated drift. \\
[[ZP_ENEMY_A_POS]] & 16-bit phase counter, decremented each  % TODO-SYM: $DE
                                 tick by [[ZP_ADVANCE_RATE]]. \\
[[ZP_ENEMY_A_ROW]] & Sprite starting row for the draw pass at
                            [[ENEMY_A_DRAW]]. \\
\end{tabular}
\end{center}

The routine runs in three phases.

\paragraph{Sound.}  A separate 8-step click timer [[ZP_ENEMY_A_SND_CTR]] selects a pitch byte from [[SND_PITCH_TBL_A]] and emits
an [[$0A]]-duration click through [[SFX_TONE]].  The timer is skipped when
negative (idle) and decremented otherwise.  The pitch table is packed
into the [[SCREEN_ROW_HELPER]] data blob and is addressed directly via
the [[SND_PITCH_TBL_A]] alias.

\paragraph{Gate.}  With [[ZP_ENEMY_A_STATE]] read: the routine returns
immediately when the slot is inactive.  A positive state value (bit~7
clear) ticks unconditionally.  A negative state value (bit~7 set) is
gated behind a low-probability PRNG draw~--- [[ZP_PRNG_A]] must
be strictly less than [[$09]], so the counter advances about one frame in  % TODO-SYM: $09
twenty-nine.  Negative-state therefore corresponds to a slow,
randomised drift while positive-state is a steady traversal.

\paragraph{Tick and rearm.}  The tick itself subtracts
[[ZP_ADVANCE_RATE]] ([[$40]], set by [[DIFFICULTY_UPDATE]] to [[$01]], [[$02]]
or [[$03]] depending on tier) from the 16-bit counter.  The rearm window
is deliberately narrow: we proceed only when the high byte
[[ZP_ENEMY_A_POS]]$+1$ has just settled to [[$00]] and the low byte is
strictly below [[$3E]].  Any 16-bit underflow leaves the high byte at [[$FF]]  % TODO-SYM: $3E $FF
and exits via [[RTS]], so the routine fires exactly once per reload
cycle as the counter steps down through the [[$0000]]..[[$003D]] band.  % TODO-SYM: $003D

Rearm then:

\begin{enumerate}
\item If the slot was in drift mode (state bit~7 set), promotes it
  back to [[$01]] (steady tick).  An already-steady slot keeps its
  current state value unchanged.
\item Unconditionally writes [[$01]] into [[ZP_ENEMY_C_STATE]]~---
  reactivating the ground-level companion slot owned by
  [[ENEMY_C_ADVANCE]] / [[ENEMY_C_DRAW]].  This is the cross-slot
  handshake: every enemy-A reload wakes up enemy-C.
\item Reloads [[ZP_ENEMY_A_POS]] to [[$0361]].  At the fastest tier  % TODO-SYM: $0361
  ([[$40]]~=~[[$03]]) the next reload is~$\lceil 0x0361/3\rceil\approx 289$
  frames away on the steady path, or~$\sim 29\times$ that on the
  PRNG-gated drift path.
\item Sets [[ZP_ENEMY_A_ROW]] to [[ZP_ENEMY_C_ROW]] $+$ [[$07]], so
  the enemy-A sprite is always drawn seven rows below the ground
  companion.
\end{enumerate}

Initial on-disk state seeds [[ZP_ENEMY_A_POS]] at [[$003E]] (right at the  % TODO-SYM: $003E
rearm threshold) and [[ZP_ENEMY_A_ROW]] at [[$A5]], so the first frame  % TODO-SYM: $A5
after [[INIT_LEVEL_STATE]] immediately reloads the counter and arms
enemy-C.

\paragraph{Cross-references.}  [[ZP_ADVANCE_RATE]] is also consumed at
[[$1675]] by the enemy-C tick; the two entities share a single  % TODO-SYM: $1675
difficulty-controlled advance rate.  The draw counterpart
[[ENEMY_A_DRAW]] at [[$1423]] reads [[ZP_ENEMY_A_STATE]],
[[ZP_ENEMY_A_POS]] and [[ZP_ENEMY_A_ROW]] directly, uses bit~7 of
[[ZP_ENEMY_A_STATE]] to gate walking animation, and on player-overlap
writes [[$00]] back to [[ZP_ENEMY_A_STATE]] to deactivate the slot
(cf.\ [[ENEMY_B_DRAW]] which writes [[$FF]] for drift-mode deferred  % TODO-SYM: $FF
deactivation).  The \texttt{DEC [[$39]]} at [[$1528]] inside  % TODO-SYM: $1528
[[ENEMY_A_DRAW]] is what consumes a player-life credit on
enemy-A/player overlap.

<<enemy a defines>>=

; --- Zero-page (enemy-A advance slot) ---
ZP_ENEMY_A_SND_CTR = $B8        ; 8-step sound-click counter (BMI = idle)
ZP_ENEMY_A_STATE   = $DC        ; Control: $00 off; +=steady; -=drift (PRNG-gated)
ZP_ENEMY_A_POS     = $DD        ; 16-bit advance counter ($DD/$DE)
ZP_ENEMY_A_ROW     = $DF        ; Sprite starting row
; Enemy-C handshake: the rearm path writes ZP_ENEMY_C_STATE and reads ZP_ENEMY_C_ROW.
ZP_ENEMY_C_STATE   = $D4        ; Companion slot state (set by enemy-A rearm)
ZP_ENEMY_C_ROW     = $D7        ; Companion slot row (source for ROW+7)
; Sound pitch table lives inside the SCREEN_ROW_HELPER hex blob.
SND_PITCH_TBL_A    = $0229      ; Pitch bytes indexed by ZP_ENEMY_A_SND_CTR

<<enemy a advance>>=

        ORG $13D6
ENEMY_A_ADVANCE:
        SUBROUTINE
        ; Per-frame tick for the enemy-A slot: play a click, gate on
        ; state/PRNG, decrement the 16-bit advance counter, and on
        ; narrow-band crossing, rearm the slot and wake enemy-C.
        ;
        ; Inputs:
        ;   ZP_ENEMY_A_SND_CTR  --- click-pitch index (BMI = idle).
        ;   ZP_ENEMY_A_STATE    --- $00 off / +steady / -drift.
        ;   ZP_ENEMY_A_POS      --- 16-bit counter.
        ;   ZP_PRNG_A           --- probability gate on drift (-) path.
        ;   ZP_ADVANCE_RATE     --- per-frame decrement ($01/$02/$03).
        ;   ZP_ENEMY_C_ROW      --- used to derive ZP_ENEMY_A_ROW on rearm.
        ;
        ; Behavior:
        ;   1. Emit a click from SND_PITCH_TBL_A[ZP_ENEMY_A_SND_CTR]
        ;      via SFX_TONE; skip when the counter is negative.
        ;   2. Exit if the slot is off; in drift mode also exit when
        ;      ZP_PRNG_A >= $09.
        ;   3. Decrement ZP_ENEMY_A_POS by ZP_ADVANCE_RATE; exit
        ;      unless the new value lies in ZP_PAGE_FLAG..$003D.
        ;   4. Rearm: promote drift->steady if needed, arm
        ;      ZP_ENEMY_C_STATE with $01, reload ZP_ENEMY_A_POS to
        ;      $0361, set ZP_ENEMY_A_ROW := ZP_ENEMY_C_ROW + 7.
        ;
        ; Modifies:
        ;   ZP_ENEMY_A_SND_CTR, ZP_ENEMY_A_STATE, ZP_ENEMY_A_POS,
        ;   ZP_ENEMY_A_ROW, ZP_ENEMY_C_STATE
        ; Clobbers: A, X, Y

; --- Emit click from pitch table ---
        LDX ZP_ENEMY_A_SND_CTR
        BMI .after_click                ; Negative = idle
        LDA SND_PITCH_TBL_A,X           ; Pitch byte
        LDX #$0A                        ; Duration = 10 clicks
        JSR SFX_TONE
        DEC ZP_ENEMY_A_SND_CTR
.after_click:

; --- State gate + PRNG probability gate on drift path ---
        LDA ZP_ENEMY_A_STATE
        BEQ .exit                       ; $00 = inactive
        BPL .tick                       ; Positive = steady: tick now
        LDA ZP_PRNG_A                   ; Negative = drift: PRNG gate
        CMP #$09
        BCS .exit                       ; $5F >= 9 -> skip this frame
        JMP .tick                       ; else tick (must hop over .exit RTS)
.exit:
        RTS

; --- 16-bit decrement; fall through to rearm only in the narrow ---
; ---   $0000..$003D band (any underflow exits via BNE).          ---
.tick:
        SEC
        LDA ZP_ENEMY_A_POS
        SBC ZP_ADVANCE_RATE
        STA ZP_ENEMY_A_POS
        LDA ZP_ENEMY_A_POS+1
        SBC #$00
        STA ZP_ENEMY_A_POS+1
        BNE .exit                       ; hi != 0 (still positive or borrow)
        LDA ZP_ENEMY_A_POS
        CMP #$3E
        BCS .exit                       ; lo >= $3E: not yet in rearm window

; --- Rearm slot and wake enemy-C ---
        LDA #$01
        BIT ZP_ENEMY_A_STATE            ; Test state bit 7
        BPL .promote_done               ; bit 7 clear (steady): leave state
        STA ZP_ENEMY_A_STATE            ; bit 7 set (drift): promote to ZP_LAST_DIR
.promote_done:
        STA ZP_ENEMY_C_STATE            ; Wake companion slot ($D4 <- $01)
        LDA #$03
        STA ZP_ENEMY_A_POS+1            ; Reload hi to ZP_PLAYER_STANCE
        LDA #$61
        STA ZP_ENEMY_A_POS              ; Reload lo to $61  (counter = $0361)
        LDA ZP_ENEMY_C_ROW
        CLC
        ADC #$07
        STA ZP_ENEMY_A_ROW              ; Row := companion row + 7
        RTS
@ %def ENEMY_A_ADVANCE
@ %def ZP_ENEMY_A_SND_CTR ZP_ENEMY_A_STATE ZP_ENEMY_A_POS ZP_ENEMY_A_ROW
@ %def ZP_ENEMY_C_STATE ZP_ENEMY_C_ROW SND_PITCH_TBL_A

\section{Enemy-A draw and player-collision}

[[ENEMY_A_DRAW]] at [[$1423]] is the draw+hit routine for the enemy-A
slot --- the third and final member of the entity-draw triplet that
mirrors [[ENEMY_B_DRAW]] (enemy-B) and [[ENEMY_C_DRAW]] (enemy-C).
Called from [[MAIN_LOOP]] every frame after [[ENEMY_A_ADVANCE]] has
ticked the slot, this routine completes the three-slot entity
system.  Previously emitted as the [[SPRITE_DRAW_1]] HEX stub; that
name is retired here.

\paragraph{Shape.}  Same state-gate / perspective-clip / main-draw /
hit-test frame as [[ENEMY_B_DRAW]] and [[ENEMY_C_DRAW]], but with a
distinctive \emph{two-sprite composite body} and a \emph{walking-frame
animation} on the steady path.  The overall layout is:
\begin{enumerate}
\item State gate: if [[ZP_ENEMY_A_STATE]] is [[$00]], exit immediately.
\item Perspective clip: same Y-indexed transform as B/C (subtract
  [[ZP_SPRITE_XREF]] from [[PERSPECTIVE_XOFF_LO]][[[ZP_PLAYER_Y]]],
  then subtract that from [[ZP_ENEMY_A_POS]]); store the result in
  [[ZP_CLIP_X_LO]]/[[ZP_CLIP_X_HI]]; exit if high byte non-zero.
  Right-edge clip is [[$9A]] (vs.\ enemy-B's [[$9C]] and enemy-C's [[$94]]).  % TODO-SYM: $9A $94
\item Common sprite-parameter setup: column from [[PROJ_SCREEN_COL]],
  frame index from [[PROJ_FRAME_IDX]], width [[$03]], height [[$13]].
\item \emph{State-polarity dispatch} (\texttt{BPL}): positive state
  (steady tick) branches to the animated path at [[$14A0]]; negative  % TODO-SYM: $14A0
  state (drift, set externally by [[ENEMY_C_DRAW]]'s hit broadcast)
  falls through to the un-animated stance path at [[$1463]].  Note:  % TODO-SYM: $1463
  this polarity is the \emph{opposite} of the convention used by
  [[ENEMY_B_DRAW]] and [[ENEMY_C_DRAW]], where negative-state jumps
  to a drift \emph{puff} and positive-state takes the main steady
  draw.  Enemy-A has no puff; drift just collapses the animation.
\item Un-animated stance ([[$1463]], reached when drift \emph{or} when  % TODO-SYM: $1463
  steady+animation-phase-0/2): draw main body at row~[[ZP_ENEMY_A_ROW]]
  from [[SPRITE_TABLE_A_BODY_LO]]/[[SPRITE_TABLE_A_BODY_HI]], then draw a $[[$03]]\times[[$03]]$ ``feet'' sprite at
  row~+~[[$13]] from [[SPRITE_TABLE_A_FEET_LO]]/[[SPRITE_TABLE_A_FEET_HI]], then \texttt{JMP} to the hit test.
\item Animated walking ([[$14A0]], reached only on steady state):  % TODO-SYM: $14A0
  extract a 2-bit phase from [[ZP_FRAME_COUNTER]] (mask [[$06]], LSR);
  if the phase is [[$00]] or [[$02]], rejoin the stance path at [[$1463]];  % TODO-SYM: $1463
  otherwise (phase [[$01]] or [[$03]], two out of every four frames)
  stash the phase in [[ZP_ENEMY_A_LEG_PHASE]] and draw the
  body at row~$-$1 plus one of two \emph{walking-feet} sprite
  variants at row~+~[[$12]] (height~[[$04]] instead of [[$03]]):  % TODO-SYM: $12
  phase [[$01]] selects [[SPRITE_TABLE_A_STEP2_LO]],
  phase [[$03]] selects [[SPRITE_TABLE_A_STEP1_LO]].
  Both variants then rejoin the hit test via fall-through or
  \texttt{JMP}.
\item Player-hit test ([[$1506]]): check if [[ZP_CLIP_X_LO]] is in the  % TODO-SYM: $1506
  window [[[$42]],[[$4F]]) \emph{and} if [[ZP_ENEMY_A_ROW]] lies in the  % TODO-SYM: $42 $4F
  $[\textrm{player}-[[$14]],\,\textrm{player}+[[$10]]]$ band ([[$24]] rows  % TODO-SYM: $14 $24
  tall, 4 rows taller than enemy-B's [[$1B]]).
\item On hit: \emph{immediately} deactivate enemy-A ([[$00]] to
  [[ZP_ENEMY_A_STATE]], \emph{not} [[$FF]]-drift like enemy-B), reload  % TODO-SYM: $FF
  [[ZP_ENEMY_A_SND_CTR]] to [[$07]] (one final death click), decrement
  [[ZP_GAME_OVER]] to consume a player-life credit, award
  +[[$0300]] BCD via [[SCORE_ADD]] (same 300~points as enemy-B), and
  exit.
\end{enumerate}

\paragraph{Why four sprite-table bases?}  Enemy-A is rendered as a
humanoid figure with distinct head/body and feet components.  The
four bases used ([[$09]], [[$10]], [[$17]], [[$1E]] in the 128-entry  % TODO-SYM: $09
[[SPRITE_TABLE_LO]]/[[SPRITE_TABLE_HI]] at [[$B000]]/[[$B080]]) correspond
to four sprite families all indexed by [[PROJ_FRAME_IDX]]:
\begin{center}
\begin{tabular}{ll}
Base [[$09]] & Main body (head/torso, $[[$03]]\times[[$13]]$) --- all paths \\  % TODO-SYM: $09
Base [[$17]] & Stance feet ($[[$03]]\times[[$03]]$) --- un-animated drift / stance frames \\
Base [[$10]] & Walking feet variant~1 ($[[$03]]\times[[$04]]$) --- steady phase [[$03]] \\
Base [[$1E]] & Walking feet variant~2 ($[[$03]]\times[[$04]]$) --- steady phase [[$01]] \\
\end{tabular}
\end{center}
Cycling phase through [[$01]] $\to$ [[$03]] on consecutive frames (with
stance frames between) produces a four-frame walking gait
(stance / step~1 / stance / step~2) tied to [[ZP_FRAME_COUNTER]]
rather than to a dedicated animation clock.

\paragraph{Cross-slot consequences.}  Enemy-A's hit path makes the
\emph{third} write to [[ZP_GAME_OVER]] in the triplet: both enemy-B
\emph{and} enemy-A count as player-life hazards, while enemy-C does
not touch [[$39]] at all (its hit target is the floor-enemy list, not
the player).  The \texttt{DEC [[$39]]} at [[$1528]] is what  % TODO-SYM: $1528
[[ENEMY_B_DRAW]]'s prior prose referenced; see the entity-triplet
cross-reference table below.  Enemy-A's hit does not broadcast any
handshake writes to other slots --- it only zeroes its own state.

\paragraph{Contrast with the rest of the triplet:}
\begin{center}
\begin{tabular}{llll}
                        & Enemy-A                        & Enemy-B                        & Enemy-C               \\ \hline
Slot state              & [[$DC]]                          & [[$E0]]                          & [[$D4]]                  \\
16-bit pos              & [[$DD]]/[[$DE]]                     & [[$E1]]/[[$E2]]                     & [[$D5]]/[[$D6]]             \\  % TODO-SYM: $DE $E2 $D6
Row                     & [[$DF]]                          & [[$E3]]                          & [[$D7]]                  \\
Main body size          & $[[$03]]\times[[$13]]$              & $[[$05]]\times[[$11]]$              & $[[$02]]\times[[$0B]]$      \\
Main body table         & [[$B009]]/[[$B089]]                 & [[$B025]]/[[$B0A5]]                 & [[$AFE1]]/[[$B061]]         \\
