        ORG $1536
ENEMY_B_ADVANCE:
        SUBROUTINE
        ; Per-frame tick for the enemy-B slot.  Structurally similar
        ; to ENEMY_A_ADVANCE / ENEMY_C_ADVANCE but counts UP toward a
        ; rearm threshold and is gated on ZP_ANIM_COUNTER rather than
        ; ZP_ADVANCE_RATE.  The per-frame add amount is self-modified
        ; to be ZP_ANIM_COUNTER itself when $1F in {1, 3}.  Rearm
        ; reloads counter to $003E, reseats row from ENEMY_C_ROW_TBL+($1F&3),
        ; and leaves state unchanged (no handshake --- see
        ; ENEMY_B_DRAW at $15FE where B writes $FF to its own state
        ; on player-overlap, deferring deactivation through the
        ; drift-path wrap).  Drift mode (state bit 7) counts up on lo
        ; only and self-deactivates on lo-byte wrap.
        ;
        ; Inputs:
        ;   ZP_ENEMY_B_SND_CTR  --- click-pitch index (BMI = idle).
        ;   ZP_ENEMY_B_STATE    --- $00 off / +steady / -drift.
        ;   ZP_ENEMY_B_POS      --- 16-bit counter (counts UP).
        ;   ZP_ANIM_COUNTER     --- gates tick rate; writes SMC byte.
        ;   ENEMY_C_ROW_TBL     --- 4-entry row table ENEMY_C_ROW_TBL..$87.
        ;
        ; Behavior:
        ;   1. Emit a click from SND_PITCH_TBL_B[ZP_ENEMY_B_SND_CTR]
        ;      via SFX_TONE; skip when the counter is negative.
        ;   2. Exit if state is $00.  Steady ($+$): fall through.
        ;      Drift ($-$): jump to .drift_tick.
        ;   3. ADD SMC_ENEMY_B_ADD to ZP_ENEMY_B_POS (16-bit).
        ;   4. If new hi byte >= $03, try rearm at .rearm_attempt.
        ;   5. Otherwise gate on ZP_ANIM_COUNTER: if $1F < $04 and
        ;      $1F not in {0, 2}, patch SMC_ENEMY_B_ADD := $1F.
        ;
        ; Modifies:
        ;   ZP_ENEMY_B_SND_CTR, ZP_ENEMY_B_STATE, ZP_ENEMY_B_POS,
        ;   ZP_ENEMY_B_ROW, SMC_ENEMY_B_ADD (self-modified code byte)
        ; Clobbers: A, X

; --- Emit click from pitch table ---
        LDX ZP_ENEMY_B_SND_CTR
        BMI .after_click                ; Negative = idle
        LDA SND_PITCH_TBL_B,X           ; Pitch byte
        LDX #$0A                        ; Duration = 10 clicks
        JSR SFX_TONE
        DEC ZP_ENEMY_B_SND_CTR
.after_click:

; --- State gate: $00 idle, $+$ steady, $-$ drift ---
        LDA ZP_ENEMY_B_STATE
        BEQ .exit                       ; $00 = inactive
        BPL .steady                     ; Positive = steady up-count
        JMP .drift_tick                 ; Negative = drift (self-destruct)

; --- Steady tick: 16-bit ADD with SMC-patched increment ---
.steady:
        CLC
        LDA ZP_ENEMY_B_POS
SMC_ENEMY_B_ADD = *+1                   ; ADC operand byte (patched below)
        ADC #$01                        ; Initial increment = $01
        STA ZP_ENEMY_B_POS
        LDA ZP_ENEMY_B_POS+1
        ADC #$00
        STA ZP_ENEMY_B_POS+1
        CMP #$03                        ; hi reached $03?
        BCS .rearm_attempt              ; yes: try rearm

; --- Gate on animation counter; patch SMC increment if $1F in {1,3} ---
        LDA ZP_ANIM_COUNTER
        CMP #$04
        BCS .exit                       ; $1F >= 4: out of range
        CMP #$00
        BEQ .exit                       ; $1F = 0: pause state
        CMP #$02
        BEQ .exit                       ; $1F = 2: pause state
        STA SMC_ENEMY_B_ADD             ; $1F in {1,3}: patch ADC #imm
.exit:
        RTS

; --- Rearm: reload counter to $003E, reseat row from ENEMY_C_ROW_TBL,X ---
.rearm_attempt:
        LDA ZP_ENEMY_B_POS
        CMP #$5A
        BCC .exit                       ; lo < $5A: still counting up
        LDA #$00
        STA ZP_ENEMY_B_POS+1            ; hi := 0
        LDA #$3E
        STA ZP_ENEMY_B_POS              ; lo := $3E (counter := $003E)
        LDA ZP_ANIM_COUNTER
        AND #$03
        TAX                             ; X = $1F & 3, range 0..3
        LDA ENEMY_C_ROW_TBL,X           ; $84/$85/$86/$87
        STA ZP_ENEMY_B_ROW
        RTS

; --- Drift path: count up on lo only; on wrap, self-deactivate ---
.drift_tick:
        INC ZP_ENEMY_B_POS
        BNE .exit                       ; No wrap: exit
        LDA #$00
        STA ZP_ENEMY_B_STATE            ; Wrap: state := $00 (deactivate)
        RTS
@ %def ENEMY_B_ADVANCE SMC_ENEMY_B_ADD
@ %def ZP_ENEMY_B_STATE ZP_ENEMY_B_POS ZP_ENEMY_B_ROW ZP_ENEMY_B_SND_CTR
@ %def SND_PITCH_TBL_B

\section{Enemy-B draw and player-collision}

[[ENEMY_B_DRAW]] at [[$1591]] is the draw+hit routine for the enemy-B
slot, and the third member of the sprite-draw family that mirrors
[[ENEMY_A_DRAW]] (enemy-A) and [[ENEMY_C_DRAW]] (enemy-C).  It is
called from [[MAIN_LOOP]] every frame after [[ENEMY_B_ADVANCE]] has
ticked the slot; the two routines together implement the enemy-B
cycle.

\paragraph{Shape.}  A short state gate -- drift dispatch -- clip --
main draw -- player-collision body, followed by a separate
drift-mode draw tail.  The overall layout is:
\begin{enumerate}
\item If [[ZP_ENEMY_B_STATE]] is~[[$00]], exit.
\item If it is \emph{negative} (drift mode, set by the collision
  body below), jump to the drift-mode draw at [[$1623]].  % TODO-SYM: $1623
\item Otherwise (steady mode) compute a screen-relative X from the
  16-bit position [[ZP_ENEMY_B_POS]] via a perspective lookup
  indexed by [[ZP_PLAYER_Y]], clip against a [[$9C]] column bound, and
  draw a [[$05]]$\times$[[$11]] sprite from [[SPRITE_TABLE_LO]]+[[$25]] /  % TODO-SYM: $25
  [[SPRITE_TABLE_HI]]+[[$25]] indexed by [[PROJ_FRAME_IDX]].  % TODO-SYM: $25
\item Player-collision test: if the clipped X is in the window
  [[[$42]],[[$55]]) and [[ZP_ENEMY_B_ROW]] lies in a  % TODO-SYM: $42 $55
  $[{\rm player\_col}-[[$0E]],\,{\rm player\_col}+[[$0D]]]$ band
  ([[$1B]] wide), the enemy has overlapped the player.
\item On overlap: write [[$FF]] to [[ZP_ENEMY_B_STATE]] (put B into  % TODO-SYM: $FF
  drift mode so it self-deactivates via the 256-frame drift-wrap in
  [[ENEMY_B_ADVANCE]]), rewind [[ZP_ENEMY_B_POS]] to
  $([[$AF]]-[[$03]])\cdot[[$100]] + [[$D0]]$, bump [[ZP_ENEMY_B_ROW]] by 2, rearm  % TODO-SYM: $D0
  the click counter ([[ZP_ENEMY_B_SND_CTR]]~=~[[$05]]), award 300~BCD
  points via [[SCORE_ADD]], and decrement the game-over flag [[$39]].
  The draw call itself is skipped on this path.
\item The drift-mode branch at [[$1623]] draws a smaller [[$02]]$\times$[[$06]]  % TODO-SYM: $1623
  ``puff'' sprite from the level-data pointer pair at [[$755A]]/[[$765A]]
  (inside the per-level swappable region).
\end{enumerate}

\paragraph{Per-frame hit cost.}  The \texttt{DEC [[$39]]} inside the
overlap body is the same shape as the one inside
[[ENEMY_A_DRAW]] (at [[$1528]]).  [[$39]] is initialized to [[$01]] by  % TODO-SYM: $1528
[[INIT_LEVEL_STATE]] and reset to [[$01]] by the player-reincarnation
code at [[$5EC3]] (see [[MAIN_LOOP]]'s game-over check at [[$6832]]).  Each  % TODO-SYM: $5EC3 $6832
enemy-A or enemy-B overlap decrements [[$39]]; once it goes negative the
main-loop tail branches to [[GAME_OVER]].  So B's overlap body is the
``player-hit'' half of the enemy-B cycle and matches A's behaviour
structurally --- though the way B absorbs the hit differs from A's:
A writes [[$00]] to [[ZP_ENEMY_A_STATE]] immediately, while B writes [[$FF]]  % TODO-SYM: $FF
to enter drift mode and lets the drift-path wrap in
[[ENEMY_B_ADVANCE]] complete the deactivation.

\paragraph{Screen-relative X via perspective lookup.}  Both
[[ENEMY_A_DRAW]] and [[ENEMY_B_DRAW]] compute
$$
  X_{\rm screen} = {\rm pos\_lo} - ({\rm PERSPECTIVE\_XOFF\_LO}[{\rm player\_Y}] - {\rm ZP\_SPRITE\_XREF}),
$$
with the high byte similarly propagated to [[$B0]].  If the high-byte
difference in [[$B0]] is non-zero after the subtract, the enemy is
off-screen horizontally and the routine returns without drawing.
Otherwise the low byte is the screen-relative X ($0$--$[[$9B]]$) used as
the index into three parallel tables:
[[PROJ_SCREEN_COL]] for the screen column,
[[PROJ_FRAME_IDX]] for the sprite-frame index within the
sprite family.  These are the same tables used by [[HAZARD_CHECK]]
for projectile rendering, so the enemy sprites share the
horizontal-position $\to$ sprite-frame mapping with projectiles.

\paragraph{Sprite family at index [[$25]].}  The steady-mode draw  % TODO-SYM: $25
indexes [[SPRITE_TABLE_LO]] / [[SPRITE_TABLE_HI]] at base [[$25]]  % TODO-SYM: $25
(addresses [[$B025]] / [[$B0A5]]).  Indexed by the sprite frame from
[[PROJ_FRAME_IDX]], this selects one of seven enemy-B body sprites
(7 frames per sprite family at this base index); compare
[[ENEMY_A_DRAW]] which uses bases [[$09]], [[$10]], [[$17]], [[$1E]] for  % TODO-SYM: $09
enemy-A's multiple sprite variants (body / walk-1 / stance-feet /
walk-2).

\paragraph{Drift-mode puff at [[$755A]]/[[$765A]].}  When
[[ZP_ENEMY_B_STATE]] is negative the draw path jumps to the short
drift-tail at [[$1623]] which patches [[SMC_DS_SRC_LO]] /  % TODO-SYM: $1623
[[SMC_DS_SRC_HI]] to the 16-bit pointer pair at [[$755A]] / [[$765A]]
--- inside the per-level swappable region [[$7500]]-[[$7AFF]] --- and  % TODO-SYM: $7500 $7AFF
draws a [[$02]]$\times$[[$06]] sprite.  The pointer is therefore
\emph{level-specific}: each level's data contributes its own
enemy-B drift-puff sprite.  This is different from the steady-mode
draw which reads from the persistent [[SPRITE_TABLE_LO]] / [[SPRITE_TABLE_HI]]
tables at [[$B000]].

\paragraph{Sprite art.}  Figure~\ref{fig:enemy_b_sprites} shows the
seven enemy-B body frames at the seven perspective depths.  The
small drift-mode puff is part of
Figure~\ref{fig:enemy_c_auxiliary} (the level-specific auxiliary
set, shared with enemy-C and the special-sprite peek marker).  All
enemy-B bytes live in the swappable region ([[$BA27]]--[[$BCF0]]) and  % TODO-SYM: $BA27 $BCF0
were extracted from [[drol.dsk]] phase~0.

