        ORG $1646
ENEMY_C_ADVANCE:
        SUBROUTINE
        ; Per-frame tick for the enemy-C ``ground companion'' slot.
        ; Mirrors ENEMY_A_ADVANCE's tick+rearm template with three
        ; key differences (see section Enemy-C advance timer):
        ;   1. Click is SND_DELAY_DOWN (descending), not SFX_TONE.
        ;   2. Drift mode bobs ZP_ENEMY_C_ROW vertically using the
        ;      frame-counter bit-4 phase, not a PRNG skip gate.
        ;   3. Rearm deactivates the slot (writes ZP_PAGE_FLAG to state) and
        ;      reseats the row from the two-entry FLOOR_THRESH/ENEMY_C_ROW_TBL table ---
        ;      it does NOT wake another slot.
        ;
        ; Inputs:
        ;   ZP_ENEMY_C_SND_CTR  --- click-pitch index (BMI = idle).
        ;   ZP_ENEMY_C_STATE    --- $00 off / +steady / -drift.
        ;   ZP_ENEMY_C_POS      --- 16-bit counter.
        ;   ZP_ADVANCE_RATE     --- per-frame decrement ($01/$02/$03).
        ;   ZP_FRAME_COUNTER    --- drives drift-mode row bobble.
        ;   ZP_PRNG_A           --- selects which row anchor on rearm.
        ;   ENEMY_C_ROW_TBL     --- 3-entry row anchor table at $85/$86/$87
        ;                          (addressed as $84,X for X in {1,2,3}).
        ;
        ; Behavior:
        ;   1. Emit a click from SND_PITCH_TBL_C[ZP_ENEMY_C_SND_CTR]
        ;      via SND_DELAY_DOWN with duration $08; skip when idle.
        ;   2. Exit if state is $00.  Steady ($+$): tick now.  Drift
        ;      ($-$): jump to .drift_tick and INC the lo counter only.
        ;   3. Steady tick: 1-in-4 frames (FD&3==3), nudge ROW $+/-$1
        ;      based on FD bit~4; then SBC ZP_ADVANCE_RATE on the
        ;      16-bit counter; rearm only if $D5 < $3C and $D6 == 0.
        ;   4. Rearm: reload counter to $0352, pick X = (PRNG_A&3)
        ;      if non-zero else 1, set ROW := $84,X - $0A, write $00
        ;      to state.
        ;
        ; Modifies:
        ;   ZP_ENEMY_C_SND_CTR, ZP_ENEMY_C_STATE, ZP_ENEMY_C_POS,
        ;   ZP_ENEMY_C_ROW
        ; Clobbers: A, X, Y

; --- Emit click from pitch table ---
        LDX ZP_ENEMY_C_SND_CTR
        BMI .after_click                ; Negative = idle
        LDA SND_PITCH_TBL_C,X           ; Pitch byte
        LDX #$08                        ; Duration = 8 clicks
        JSR SND_DELAY_DOWN
        DEC ZP_ENEMY_C_SND_CTR
.after_click:

; --- State gate: $00 idle, $+$ steady, $-$ drift ---
        LDA ZP_ENEMY_C_STATE
        BEQ .exit                       ; $00 = inactive (RTS at $1681)
        BPL .steady                     ; Positive = steady tick
        JMP .drift_tick                 ; Negative = drift tick (counter +1)

; --- Steady path: drift-mode row bobble runs on 1-in-4 frames ---
.steady:
        LDA ZP_FRAME_COUNTER
        AND #$03
        CMP #$03
        BNE .tick                       ; Other 3/4 frames: skip bobble
        LDA ZP_FRAME_COUNTER
        AND #$10                        ; Phase: bit 4 flips every 16 frames
        BNE .row_dec
        INC ZP_ENEMY_C_ROW              ; Phase 0: bobble down
        JMP .tick
.row_dec:
        DEC ZP_ENEMY_C_ROW              ; Phase 1: bobble up

; --- 16-bit decrement; rearm only on the narrow $0000..$003B band ---
.tick:
        LDA ZP_ENEMY_C_POS
        SEC
        SBC ZP_ADVANCE_RATE
        STA ZP_ENEMY_C_POS
        LDA ZP_ENEMY_C_POS+1
        SBC #$00
        STA ZP_ENEMY_C_POS+1
        BEQ .check_lo                   ; hi == 0: maybe rearm
.exit:
        RTS                             ; hi != 0: still ticking, exit
.check_lo:
        LDA ZP_ENEMY_C_POS
        CMP #$3C
        BCS .exit                       ; lo >= $3C: not yet in window

; --- Rearm: reload counter, pick row anchor, deactivate self ---
.rearm:
        LDA #$52
        STA ZP_ENEMY_C_POS              ; Reload lo to ZP_INPUT_1
        LDA #$03
        STA ZP_ENEMY_C_POS+1            ; Reload hi to ZP_PLAYER_STANCE (counter = $0352)
        LDA ZP_PRNG_A
        AND #$03
        BNE .have_idx                   ; PRNG&3 != 0: X := 1, 2, or 3
        LDA #$01                        ; PRNG&3 == 0: force X := 1
.have_idx:
        TAX                             ; X in {1, 2, 3}
        LDA ENEMY_C_ROW_TBL,X           ; $85, $86, or $87: row anchor
        SEC
        SBC #$0A
        STA ZP_ENEMY_C_ROW              ; Row := anchor - $0A
        LDA #$00
        STA ZP_ENEMY_C_STATE            ; Deactivate self (state := $00)
        RTS

; --- Drift path: counter counts UP; on lo-byte overflow fall to .rearm ---
.drift_tick:
        INC ZP_ENEMY_C_POS
        BNE .exit                       ; No overflow: exit
        JMP .rearm                      ; Lo wrapped: jump to rearm reload
@ %def ENEMY_C_ADVANCE
@ %def ZP_ENEMY_C_SND_CTR ZP_ENEMY_C_POS SND_PITCH_TBL_C ENEMY_C_ROW_TBL

\section{Enemy-C draw and enemy-slot collision}

[[ENEMY_C_DRAW]] at [[$16AC]] is the draw+hit routine for the enemy-C
slot --- the third member of the sprite-draw family alongside
[[ENEMY_A_DRAW]] (enemy-A) and [[ENEMY_B_DRAW]] (enemy-B).
Called from [[MAIN_LOOP]] immediately after [[ENEMY_C_ADVANCE]] has
ticked the slot.  (Previously mislabeled \texttt{PLAYER\_RENDER} in
the stub; that name was a misnomer and is retired here --- this
routine does not draw the player at all.)

\paragraph{Shape.}  Same state-gate / perspective-clip / main-draw /
hit-test / drift-draw-tail shape as [[ENEMY_B_DRAW]], with three
substantive differences:
\begin{enumerate}
\item \textbf{Body sprite is smaller.}  [[ENEMY_B_DRAW]] draws a
  $[[$05]]\times[[$11]]$ body; enemy-C's body is a narrow $[[$02]]\times[[$0B]]$
  sprite read from [[SPRITE_TABLE_C_LO]] / [[SPRITE_TABLE_C_HI]] at
  [[$AFE1]]/[[$B061]] (indexed by [[PROJ_FRAME_IDX]]).  The column bound
  is [[$94]] rather than [[$9C]], so enemy-C clips slightly sooner at the  % TODO-SYM: $94
  right edge.
\item \textbf{Secondary ``tail'' sprite below the body.}  Immediately
  after the main draw, enemy-C issues a \emph{second} [[DRAW_SPRITE]]
  call for a $[[$01]]\times[[$07]]$ sprite at (clip\_X$-$1, row $+$ [[$0B]]),
  reading from the level-specific pointer pair
  [[ENEMY_C_TAIL_LO]]/[[ENEMY_C_TAIL_HI]] at [[$7549]]/[[$7649]] (also
  indexed by [[PROJ_FRAME_IDX]]).  The tail lives in the per-level
  swappable region [[$7500]]--[[$7AFF]] so each level contributes its own  % TODO-SYM: $7500 $7AFF
  tail art.  A \texttt{BCS} at [[$1706]] skips both the second draw and  % TODO-SYM: $1706
  the hit test if the shifted X underflowed (i.e.\ clip\_X was [[$00]]).
\item \textbf{Hit target is a 4-slot enemy table, not the player.}
  The hit test at [[$1730]]--[[$1755]] walks the four-slot floor-enemy  % TODO-SYM: $1730 $1755
  table at [[$9B]]/[[$9F]]/[[$A3]] (the same slots the beam targets), scanning
  X~=~3..0 for the first active flag.  The test compares enemy-C's
  screen-X ([[ZP_CLIP_X_LO]]) against [[ZP_ENEMY_COL]] and its row
  ([[ZP_ENEMY_C_ROW]]) against [[ZP_ENEMY_Y]].  On a match,
  enemy-C \emph{consumes} the floor-enemy slot.
\end{enumerate}

\paragraph{Hit action ([[$1757]]--[[$1782]]): the C$\rightarrow$\{A,C\}  % TODO-SYM: $1757 $1782
broadcast.}  On a hit:
\begin{enumerate}
\item Write [[$FF]] to [[ZP_ENEMY_C_STATE]] (put self into drift mode,  % TODO-SYM: $FF
  triggering the vertical bobble animation in [[ENEMY_C_ADVANCE]]).
\item If [[ZP_ENEMY_A_STATE]] is non-zero, write [[$FF]] to it too ---  % TODO-SYM: $FF
  putting enemy-A into PRNG-gated drift mode.  This is the
  \emph{cross-slot broadcast}: C's hit animates both itself and A.
\item Reload [[ZP_ENEMY_C_POS]] to ($\$$AF,$\$$D0) (hi~=~clip\_X,
  lo~=~[[$D0]]) and bump [[ZP_ENEMY_C_ROW]] by 2.  % TODO-SYM: $D0
\item Clear the floor-enemy slot: \texttt{STA [[$9B]],X} with A~=~[[$00]]
  retires the same slot the beam would retire on a laser kill.
\item Rearm the click counter ([[ZP_ENEMY_C_SND_CTR]] [[$B7]]~=~[[$04]]).
\item Award \textbf{100~BCD} points via [[SCORE_ADD]] (addend
  [[$0100]]).  Note: unlike [[ENEMY_B_DRAW]], enemy-C does
  \emph{not} decrement [[ZP_GAME_OVER]] --- this hit path is not a
  player-life event.
\end{enumerate}

\paragraph{Hit-box.}  Screen-X window is (clip\_X$-$[[$08]], clip\_X]
(enemy-C's X $\pm$ 4 pixels of the target's column); Y window is
(row$-$[[$04]], row$+$[[$0A]]) (a 13-row band centred four rows above
enemy-C's top).  Only the \emph{first} active slot (highest X with
the flag set) is tested per frame.

\paragraph{Drift-mode tail at [[$1783]].}  Reached when  % TODO-SYM: $1783
[[ZP_ENEMY_C_STATE]] is negative (set by the hit path above, or
externally by [[ENEMY_A_ADVANCE]]'s rearm at [[$1411]] which writes  % TODO-SYM: $1411
[[$01]] --- wait, only hits write [[$FF]]; A's rearm writes [[$01]] for  % TODO-SYM: $FF
steady mode).  The drift-mode draw emits a single $[[$02]]\times[[$06]]$
``puff'' sprite at [[ZP_ENEMY_C_POS]]$+1$'s column index, reading
from [[ENEMY_C_PUFF_LO]]/[[ENEMY_C_PUFF_HI]] at [[$7559]]/[[$7659]] ---
a different level-specific pointer pair from [[ENEMY_B_DRAW]]'s
[[$755A]]/[[$765A]] puff (one byte earlier).

\paragraph{Contrast with [[ENEMY_B_DRAW]]:}

