\paragraph{Topology restated.}  The C$\rightarrow$\{A,C\} broadcast
in this routine is triggered by enemy-C striking a floor-enemy, not
by striking the player.  Combined with enemy-A's rearm writing
[[$01]] to [[$D4]] (A$\rightarrow$C wake), the three-slot handshake graph
is: A wakes C on its own rearm; C arms both itself and A into drift
mode when it kills a floor-enemy; B has no outgoing handshake and
only affects its own state.

