<<game engine A prologue>>=

        ORG $614B
        SUBROUTINE
        ; Game engine prologue ($614B-$61EF, 165 bytes): movement-tick
        ; handler bodies.  Entry points called by [[PLAYER_MOVE_TICK]]:
        ;   $614B  [[PLAYER_TICK_MOVE_LEFT]]
        ;   $6184  [[PLAYER_TICK_IDLE]]
        ;   $619A  [[PLAYER_TICK_MOVE_RIGHT]]
        ;   $61E4  [[CLEAR_DRAW_PAGE]]: BIT [[ZP_PAGE_FLAG]]; page-gated
        ;                                [[CLEAR_PAGE1]]/[[CLEAR_PAGE2]].
        ; The per-frame tick chain that each movement handler invokes is:
        ;   JSR CLEAR_DRAW_PAGE  ($61E4)  --- zero the drawing page
        ;   JSR TEXT_ROW_DISPATCH ($636C) --- text-strip restore
        ;   JSR REFRESH_LEFT_WALL --- left-edge wall
        ;   JSR REFRESH_RIGHT_WALL --- right-edge wall
        ;   JSR GAME_ENGINE_A_STUB_62CA --- floor-edge background
        ;   JSR REFRESH_PILLARS   --- six landmark pillars
        ;   JSR GAME_ENGINE_A_STUB_6321 ($6321) --- entity-X redraw loop
