\section{Speaker click / delay loop}

[[SFX_TONE]] at [[$67C1]] is the game's sole sound-effect generator.  It is
called from about eight sites --- the attract hazard animation, the
projectile hazard handler, the level-intro countdown tick, the
no-more-lives fanfare, and several level/game-event paths.

The routine is a classic Apple~II nested delay-loop speaker click:

\begin{itemize}
\item The accumulator on entry sets the pitch --- the number of
  inner-loop iterations (each about 7 cycles) before one speaker click.
\item The X register on entry sets the duration --- the number of
  clicks to emit.
\item The speaker access is done indirectly through zero-page pointer
  [[$36]]/[[$37]].  The high byte at [[$37]] is [[$C0]] (set at boot and never  % TODO-SYM: $37 $C0
  modified).  The low byte at [[$36]], [[ZP_SFX_CLICK]], is either [[$30]]  % TODO-SYM: $30
  (points at [[SW_SPEAKER]] = [[$C030]], clicks the speaker) when sound is
  enabled, or [[$20]] (points at the unused cassette-output soft-switch
  [[$C020]], silent) when sound is muted.  % TODO-SYM: $C020
\end{itemize}

Making the speaker address data-driven this way lets the Ctrl-S mute
toggle (in [[INPUT_PROCESS]]) change sound state by flipping a single
bit in a ZP variable, with no branches on the hot path --- the
speaker-click instruction ([[CMP ($36),Y]]) still executes every
duration cycle but silently reads from an unused soft-switch when sound
is off.

The inner [[DEY/BNE]] loop also decrements Y back to zero before the
[[CMP ($36),Y]], so the indirect load always uses offset zero; the
wrap-around is harmless because every call enters with Y saved by the
[[TAY]] at the top of the outer loop.

<<sfx tone>>=

        ORG $67C1
SFX_TONE:
        SUBROUTINE
        ; Speaker-click tone / delay generator.
        ;
        ; Inputs:
        ;   A              --- pitch (inner-loop count, cycles per click).
        ;   X              --- duration (number of clicks to emit).
        ;   ZP_SFX_CLICK   --- low byte of speaker-click pointer
        ;                      ($30 = click $C030, $20 = silent $C020).
        ;   $37            --- high byte of speaker-click pointer, = $C0.
        ;
        ; Behavior:
        ;   Outer loop (X iterations): TAY loads Y from pitch, the
        ;   DEY/BNE inner loop counts Y down to 0 (about 5*A + 5 cycles
        ;   of delay), then CMP,Y reads through the ZP pointer.
        ;   When ZP_SFX_CLICK points this toggles the speaker;
        ;   when it points at $C020 the read is silent.  X is then
        ;   decremented; when X reaches 0 the routine returns.
        ;
        ; Clobbers: A is preserved (CMP does not modify A), X=0 on exit, Y=0.

        TAY                     ; Y = pitch (reload every outer iteration)
.delay:
        DEY
        BNE .delay              ; Inner delay: Y counts down to 0
        CMP (ZP_SFX_CLICK),Y    ; Y=0; read $C030 (click) or $C020 (silent)
        DEX
        BNE SFX_TONE            ; Next click (reloads Y from A via TAY)
        RTS
@ %def SFX_TONE

\section{Entity draw dispatcher}

[[DRAW_ENTITIES]] at [[$683C]] is the last drawing call in [[MAIN_LOOP]]
(before [[POST_FRAME]] and the exit checks).  Despite the old
``page-flip'' nickname it does \emph{not} flip the hardware page --- that
is [[DISPLAY_PAGE_FLIP]] at [[$6138]].  Instead it is the frame-level
``restore-and-draw'' dispatcher for four independent sprite categories,
each with its own state table:

\begin{enumerate}
\item A small ``hit-entity'' restore pass (phase~1) that scans a 12-slot
  active table at [[ENTITY_HIT_STATE]] ([[$8D]],X bounded by [[ZP_HIT_MAX]]
  at [[$41]]).  For the first active slot it restores two bytes of hi-res
  background at an address assembled from [[HIT_BG_HI]] ([[$0328]],X),
  [[HIT_BG_LO]] ([[$0334]],X) and the saved pixel pair [[HIT_BG_BYTE1]]
  ([[$0340]],X) / [[HIT_BG_BYTE0]] ([[$034C]],X).  The high byte is bumped by
  [[$20]] when [[ZP_PAGE_FLAG]] is negative so that the restore lands on the
  currently hidden hi-res page.  Control falls through into phase~2.
\item The \emph{player} sprite draw (phase~2, [[$6865]]--[[$68B1]]), gated on  % TODO-SYM: $6865 $68B1
  [[$0E]] being non-negative.  The player column ([[ZP_PLAYER_Y]]+[[$10]])
  is looked up in parallel tables [[FLOOR_SPRITE_IDX]] and
  [[FLOOR_SCREEN_COL]] to produce a sprite-frame index and
  screen column.  Frame-counter bit~2 ([[$FD]]) selects between two
  sprite-data address tables (offsets [[$7542]]/[[$7642]] and [[$7552]]/[[$7652]])  % TODO-SYM: $7542 $7642 $7552 $7652
  whose entries are copied into the SMC operand slot inside the
  playfield sprite blitter at [[DRAW_SPRITE_PLAYFIELD]] ([[$65D5]],
  operand bytes at [[SMC_PFB_SRC_LO]] / [[SMC_PFB_SRC_HI]] = [[$6615]] /
  [[$6616]]).  The sprite row is [[FLOOR_TO_ROW]] indexed either
  by [[ZP_INTRO_Y]] during the intro/wait phase or by
  [[ZP_PLAYER_COL]] during gameplay --- selected by
  [[$1E]]~(zero means intro is still running).
\item A single ``special'' sprite (phase~3, [[$68B2]]--[[$6904]]) --- most  % TODO-SYM: $68B2 $6904
  likely the moon-bouncing ball or an attract-mode actor --- gated on
  [[$AB]] being strictly positive.  Its floor-column index ([[$AC]]) is
  converted to an absolute screen position using [[FLOOR_BASE_ROW]] plus an offset [[$B9]],X (X from [[$AD]]), minus~[[$08]].  The
  result indexes [[FLOOR_SPRITE_IDX]]/[[FLOOR_SCREEN_COL]] the same way
  as phase~2; sprite-data table pair is [[$7594]]/[[$7694]] or [[$759B]]/[[$769B]]  % TODO-SYM: $7594 $7694 $759B $769B
  (bit~2 of frame counter), row comes from [[FLOOR_TO_ROW]] indexed by
  [[$AE]].
\item A two-slot ``companion'' draw (phase~4, [[$6905]]--[[$694D]]), gated on  % TODO-SYM: $6905 $694D
  [[$33]] being non-negative.  Iterates X=1 down to 0 through three
  parallel per-slot tables in low ZP ([[$11,X]] = floor column,
  [[$13,X]] = X-offset, [[$15,X]] = floor row index).  Each slot uses
  the fixed sprite-data table at [[$75CC]]/[[$76CC]] (no animation toggle).  % TODO-SYM: $75CC $76CC
\item A 20-slot ``entity'' draw (phase~5, [[$694E]]--[[$699B]]).  Iterates  % TODO-SYM: $694E $699B
  Y=[[$13]] down to 0 through [[ENTITY_ACTIVE]] ([[$03A8]], activity), skipping
  slots that are zero or negative.  Parallel tables provide the
  floor-column ([[ENTITY_FLOOR_COL]] = [[$0358]]), X-offset index
  ([[ENTITY_XOFF_IDX]] = [[$036C]]), and floor row index
  ([[ENTITY_FLOOR_POS]] = [[$0380]]).  All twenty slots share the same
  sprite-data table at [[$75D4]]/[[$76D4]].  % TODO-SYM: $75D4 $76D4
\end{enumerate}

Phases~2--5 each set up ZP sprite parameters ([[ZP_SPRITE_W]]/[[\_H]]
at [[$56]]/[[$57]], [[ZP_SPRITE_Y]] at [[$5B]], [[ZP_SPRITE_X]] at [[$5D]]) and
then [[JSR DRAW_SPRITE_PLAYFIELD]] --- the playfield variant of
[[DRAW_SPRITE]] at [[$65D5]] whose inner loop rejects column~[[$0B]] (the
left playfield wall) and every column \$$\ge$~[[$1C]] (the right-side  % TODO-SYM: $1C
HISCORE HUD panel), so gameplay sprites can't overwrite those fixed
screen regions.  They all patch the \emph{same} SMC operand bytes
([[$6615]]/[[$6616]] = [[SMC_PFB_SRC_LO]] / [[SMC_PFB_SRC_HI]]) inside that
blitter with sprite-specific source addresses before calling it.

The widths, heights and column indices per phase are:

\begin{center}
\begin{tabular}{l|l|l|l|l}
Phase & [[$56]] (W) & [[$57]] (H) & Source base & State gate \\
\hline
Player      & 1 & 4 & [[$7542]]/[[$7552]] & [[$0E]] $\ge$ 0 \\  % TODO-SYM: $7542 $7552
Special     & 1 & 3 & [[$7594]]/[[$759B]] & [[$AB]] $>$ 0 \\  % TODO-SYM: $7594 $759B
Companion   & 1 & 2 & [[$75CC]]        & [[$33]] $\ge$ 0 \\  % TODO-SYM: $75CC
Entities    & 1 & 5 & [[$75D4]]        & [[$03A8]],Y $>$ 0 \\  % TODO-SYM: $75D4
\end{tabular}
\end{center}

\paragraph{Why this is the ``page-flip'' in MAIN\_LOOP.}  The routine
is called immediately after [[DISPLAY_UPDATE]] and before the frame
counter increment / [[POST_FRAME]] epilogue.  It is the final step
that commits all of the frame's sprite pixels to the hidden hi-res
page, which will become visible after [[DISPLAY_PAGE_FLIP]] runs on
the next frame.  The ``flip'' in the original label referred to the
[[ZP_PAGE_FLAG]]-driven [[$20]] page-offset applied in phase~1, not to
any toggle of the display soft-switch.

\paragraph{Cross-reference to [[LEVEL_INTRO_TICK]].}  Earlier prose
speculated that this chunk patches the same [[SMC_SR_HEIGHT]] /
[[SMC_SR_YSRC]] operands inside [[DRAW_PLAYER]]
that [[LEVEL_INTRO_TICK]] patches.  That was incorrect --- this
routine does \emph{not} touch those operands.  The two SMC slots
[[DRAW_ENTITIES]] patches are [[SMC_PFB_SRC_LO]] and
[[SMC_PFB_SRC_HI]], which are the source-address operand
bytes of the sprite-data fetch inside [[DRAW_SPRITE_PLAYFIELD]] at [[$6614]].  % TODO-SYM: $6614

<<draw entities defines>>=

; --- Zero-page (entity draw dispatcher) ---
ZP_HIT_MAX      = $41           ; Max active hit-entity slot index (phase 1)
ZP_HIT_GATE     = $0E           ; $ff = suppress player draw (phase 2)
ZP_SPECIAL_A    = $AB           ; Special sprite state flag (phase 3)
ZP_SPECIAL_X    = $AC           ; Special sprite floor column (phase 3)
ZP_SPECIAL_Y    = $AD           ; Special sprite X-offset index (phase 3)
ZP_SPECIAL_ROW  = $AE           ; Special sprite floor row (phase 3)
ZP_COMPANION_GATE = $33         ; Companion-slot gate (phase 4)
ZP_COMPANION_COL  = $11         ; Companion floor-column pair (phase 4)
ZP_COMPANION_OFF  = $13         ; Companion X-offset pair (phase 4)
ZP_COMPANION_ROW  = $15         ; Companion floor-row pair (phase 4)
ZP_DRAW_DEST_LO = $FB           ; Phase-1 BG restore destination pointer (2 bytes)
ZP_DRAW_LOOP_IDX = $5C          ; Saved loop index for phases 4/5

; --- Hit-entity background-save tables (12 slots, parallel to ENTITY_HIT_STATE) ---
ENTITY_HIT_STATE = $8D          ; Hit-entity active flags ($8D,X, X<=ZP_HIT_MAX)
HIT_BG_HI       = $0328         ; High byte of BG-restore address (page 1 base)
HIT_BG_LO       = $0334         ; Low byte of BG-restore address
HIT_BG_BYTE1    = $0340         ; Saved BG byte at offset +1
HIT_BG_BYTE0    = $034C         ; Saved BG byte at offset +0

; --- 20-slot entity draw tables (phase 5) ---
; ENTITY_ACTIVE is defined as a label in the entity-tables chunk.
ENTITY_FLOOR_COL = $0358        ; Entity floor-column index table
ENTITY_XOFF_IDX = $036C          ; Entity X-offset index table
ENTITY_FLOOR_POS = $0380         ; Entity floor-row index table

; --- Floor-position lookup tables (player coord -> screen coords) ---
FLOOR_TO_ROW    = $1D40         ; Floor position -> sprite Y row
FLOOR_SPRITE_IDX = $1E00         ; Floor position -> sprite-frame index
FLOOR_SCREEN_COL = $1F00         ; Floor position -> sprite X column
FLOOR_BASE_ROW  = $188F          ; Floor-column -> base row (phase 3/4/5)

; --- DRAW_SPRITE_PLAYFIELD SMC aliases ---
; SMC_PFB_SRC_LO / SMC_PFB_SRC_HI are declared inline in the
; DRAW_SPRITE_PLAYFIELD chunk as "= *+1" / "= *+2" labels on the
; sprite-data LDA at $6614.  Each caller here patches them with the
; sprite-specific source address before JSR DRAW_SPRITE_PLAYFIELD.

@

<<draw entities>>=

        ORG $683C
DRAW_ENTITIES:
        SUBROUTINE
        ; Per-frame entity draw dispatcher --- final drawing step of
        ; MAIN_LOOP.  Restores one hit-entity's hi-res background then
        ; draws player, one special, two companions and up to twenty
        ; entities onto the hidden hi-res page.
        ;
        ; Inputs:
        ;   ZP_HIT_MAX          --- max hit-entity slot to scan.
        ;   ENTITY_HIT_STATE,X  --- per-slot active flag.
        ;   HIT_BG_HI / HIT_BG_LO     --- BG-restore destination (page 1).
        ;   HIT_BG_BYTE0 / HIT_BG_BYTE1 --- saved BG byte pair.
        ;   ZP_PAGE_FLAG b7     --- negative: restore to page 2
        ;                                 (add $20 to HIT_BG_HI).
        ;   ZP_HIT_GATE         --- negative: skip player draw.
        ;   ZP_PLAYER_Y         --- player floor position (+$10).
        ;   ZP_HIT_FLAG         --- game-state word ($00 = intro).
        ;   ZP_INTRO_Y          --- intro sprite Y source.
        ;   ZP_PLAYER_COL       --- player sprite Y source.
        ;   $FD bit 2                 --- player/special animation phase.
        ;   ZP_SPECIAL_A..ROW ($AB-$AE) --- special-sprite slot state.
        ;   ZP_COMPANION_GATE   --- companion-slot gate.
        ;   ZP_COMPANION_COL/OFF/ROW  --- 2 companion slots ($11-$16).
        ;   ENTITY_ACTIVE ($03A8..$03BB) + parallel tables
        ;     ENTITY_FLOOR_COL, ENTITY_XOFF_IDX,
        ;     ENTITY_FLOOR_POS.
        ;   FLOOR_TO_ROW / FLOOR_SPRITE_IDX / FLOOR_SCREEN_COL /
        ;     FLOOR_BASE_ROW lookup tables.
        ;
        ; Behavior:
        ;   Phase 1 scans ENTITY_HIT_STATE top-down for the first active
        ;   slot, then writes HIT_BG_BYTE0/BYTE1 back into,Y=0/1
        ;   where ($FC,$FB) is assembled from HIT_BG_HI (+$20 if the
        ;   page flag is negative) and HIT_BG_LO.  Falls through.
        ;   Phases 2--5 each set sprite dimensions / position, patch
        ;   SMC_PFB_SRC_LO/HI with a sprite-data source address, load
        ;   FLOOR_TO_ROW into ZP_SPRITE_Y and JSR DRAW_SPRITE_PLAYFIELD.
        ;
        ; Modifies:
        ;   SMC_PFB_SRC_LO / SMC_PFB_SRC_HI,
        ;   ZP_DRAW_DEST_LO, ZP_DRAW_DEST_HI ($FC),
        ;   ZP_DRAW_LOOP_IDX, ZP_SPRITE_W/H,
        ;   ZP_SPRITE_Y/X, hi-res page framebuffers.
        ; Clobbers: A, X, Y

; --- Phase 1: find topmost active hit-entity, restore its BG ---
.hit_scan:
        LDX ZP_HIT_MAX                  ; Start at highest slot
.hit_next:
        LDA ENTITY_HIT_STATE,X          ; Active flag
        BPL .hit_restore                ;   bit 7 clear = active
        DEX
        BPL .hit_next
        BMI .draw_player                ; X wrapped to $FF --- no hits
.hit_restore:
        LDA HIT_BG_HI,X                 ; High byte of saved BG address
        BIT ZP_PAGE_FLAG
        BPL .hit_bg_page1               ;   page flag positive: use as-is
        CLC
        ADC #$20                        ;   page flag negative: bump to page 2
.hit_bg_page1:
        STA ZP_DRAW_DEST_LO+1           ; ($FC) = high byte
        LDA HIT_BG_LO,X
        STA ZP_DRAW_DEST_LO             ; = low byte
        LDA HIT_BG_BYTE1,X              ; Saved pixel byte @ +1
        LDY #$01
        STA (ZP_DRAW_DEST_LO),Y         ; Restore to hi-res
        DEY
        LDA HIT_BG_BYTE0,X              ; Saved pixel byte @ +0
        STA (ZP_DRAW_DEST_LO),Y
;       fall through to phase 2

; --- Phase 2: player sprite ---
.draw_player:
        LDA ZP_HIT_GATE                 ; $0E
        BMI .draw_special               ;   negative = suppress player
        LDA ZP_PLAYER_Y                 ; Player floor position
        CLC
        ADC #$10                        ;   + $10 (centre adjust)
        TAX
        TAY                             ; X = Y = player + $10
        LDA FLOOR_SPRITE_IDX,X          ; Sprite-frame index
        TAX
        LDA FLOOR_SCREEN_COL,Y          ; Screen column
        STA ZP_SPRITE_X
        LDA $FD                         ; Frame counter
        AND #$04                        ; Bit 2 = animation phase
        BEQ .player_frameA
        LDA $7552,X                     ; Frame B source low
        STA SMC_PFB_SRC_LO
        LDA $7652,X                     ; Frame B source high
        STA SMC_PFB_SRC_HI
        JMP .player_dims
.player_frameA:
        LDA $7542,X                     ; Frame A source low
        STA SMC_PFB_SRC_LO
        LDA $7642,X                     ; Frame A source high
        STA SMC_PFB_SRC_HI
.player_dims:
        LDA #$01
        STA ZP_SPRITE_W                 ; Width = 1 byte
        LDA #$04
        STA ZP_SPRITE_H                 ; Height = 4 rows
        LDX ZP_INTRO_Y                  ; Default: intro Y source
        LDA ZP_HIT_FLAG                 ; $1E
        BEQ .player_row                 ;   $00 = intro running, keep $17
        LDX ZP_PLAYER_COL               ; Gameplay: use player column
.player_row:
        LDA FLOOR_TO_ROW,X
        STA ZP_SPRITE_Y
        JSR DRAW_SPRITE_PLAYFIELD

; --- Phase 3: special sprite (moon-ball / attract actor) ---
.draw_special:
        LDA ZP_SPECIAL_A                ; $AB
        BEQ .draw_companions            ;   $00 = inactive
        BPL .special_active             ;   positive = active
        BMI .draw_companions            ;   negative = inactive
.special_active:
        LDX ZP_SPECIAL_X                ; Floor column
        LDA FLOOR_BASE_ROW,X            ; Base floor row
        LDX ZP_SPECIAL_Y                ; X-offset index
        CLC
        ADC $B9,X                       ; + per-entity vertical offset
        SEC
        SBC #$08                        ; - 8
        TAX
        LDA FLOOR_SCREEN_COL,X
        STA ZP_SPRITE_X
        LDA #$01
        STA ZP_SPRITE_W
        LDA #$03
        STA ZP_SPRITE_H
        LDA FLOOR_SPRITE_IDX,X
        TAX
        LDA $FD
        AND #$04
        BEQ .special_frameA
        LDA $759B,X
        STA SMC_PFB_SRC_LO
        LDA $769B,X
        STA SMC_PFB_SRC_HI
        JMP .special_row
.special_frameA:
        LDA $7594,X
        STA SMC_PFB_SRC_LO
        LDA $7694,X
        STA SMC_PFB_SRC_HI
.special_row:
        LDA ZP_SPECIAL_ROW              ; $AE
        TAX
        LDA FLOOR_TO_ROW,X
        STA ZP_SPRITE_Y
        JSR DRAW_SPRITE_PLAYFIELD

; --- Phase 4: two companion-slot sprites ---
.draw_companions:
        LDA ZP_COMPANION_GATE           ; $33
        BMI .draw_entity_list
        LDX #$01                        ; Slots 1 then 0
.companion_loop:
        LDA ZP_COMPANION_COL,X          ; Floor column ($11,$12)
        TAY
        LDA FLOOR_BASE_ROW,Y            ; Base row
        STX ZP_DRAW_LOOP_IDX            ; Save X
        PHA                             ;   and accumulator
        LDA ZP_COMPANION_OFF,X          ; X-offset ($13,$14)
        TAX
        PLA
        CLC
        ADC $B9,X                       ; + offset
        SEC
        SBC #$05                        ; - 5
        TAY
        LDA FLOOR_SCREEN_COL,Y
        STA ZP_SPRITE_X
        LDA #$01
        STA ZP_SPRITE_W
        LDA #$02
        STA ZP_SPRITE_H
        LDA FLOOR_SPRITE_IDX,Y
        TAY
        LDA $75CC,Y                     ; Fixed source (no animation toggle)
        STA SMC_PFB_SRC_LO
        LDA $76CC,Y
        STA SMC_PFB_SRC_HI
        LDX ZP_DRAW_LOOP_IDX
        LDA ZP_COMPANION_ROW,X          ; Row index ($15,$16)
        TAX
        LDA FLOOR_TO_ROW,X
        STA ZP_SPRITE_Y
        JSR DRAW_SPRITE_PLAYFIELD
        LDX ZP_DRAW_LOOP_IDX
        DEX
        BPL .companion_loop

; --- Phase 5: 20-slot entity list ---
.draw_entity_list:
        LDY #$13                        ; 20 slots
.entity_next:
        LDA ENTITY_ACTIVE,Y
        BEQ .entity_step                ;   $00 = inactive
        BMI .entity_step                ;   negative = inactive
        LDA ENTITY_FLOOR_COL,Y
        TAX
        LDA FLOOR_BASE_ROW,X
        PHA
        LDA ENTITY_XOFF_IDX,Y
        TAX
        PLA
        CLC
        ADC $B9,X
        SEC
        SBC #$05
        TAX
        LDA FLOOR_SCREEN_COL,X
        STA ZP_SPRITE_X
        LDA #$01
        STA ZP_SPRITE_W
        LDA #$05
        STA ZP_SPRITE_H
        LDA FLOOR_SPRITE_IDX,X
        TAX
        LDA $75D4,X
        STA SMC_PFB_SRC_LO
        LDA $76D4,X
        STA SMC_PFB_SRC_HI
        LDA ENTITY_FLOOR_POS,Y
        TAX
        LDA FLOOR_TO_ROW,X
        STA ZP_SPRITE_Y
        STY ZP_DRAW_LOOP_IDX
        JSR DRAW_SPRITE_PLAYFIELD
        LDY ZP_DRAW_LOOP_IDX
.entity_step:
        DEY
        BPL .entity_next
        RTS
@ %def DRAW_ENTITIES

\section{Level intro / countdown tick}

[[LEVEL_INTRO_TICK]] at [[$699C]] is the first subroutine called by
[[MAIN_LOOP]] each frame.  It implements the state machine that runs
between level transitions:

\begin{itemize}
\item When [[$1E]] is positive, the game is already running and this
  routine simply returns --- main-loop work proceeds normally.
\item When [[$1E]] is negative ([[$FF]] --- just after game start or a  % TODO-SYM: $FF
  level transition), one-shot initialisation kicks in: the four
  movement slots, the input dispatcher slot and the sprite-render slot
  in the main loop are all patched to [[BIT]] ([[$2C]]) so that player
  control and sprite output are suspended during the intro.  Various
  state bytes are cleared; the countdown counter [[$18]] is set to
  [[$12]] (18 frames) and the auto-start timeout [[$19]] is set to [[$40]].  % TODO-SYM: $12
\item Once initialised ([[$1E == 0]]), the routine animates a
  countdown on every frame.  While [[$18 > 0]] it decrements $18 on
  odd frames and plays a tone/delay pulse through [[SFX_TONE]] with
  an amplitude fetched from the level-data byte [[$0200,$18]]; it also
  refreshes a sprite with a frame-dependent mask by patching the
  [[BIT]] slot at [[$65B7]] in [[DRAW_SPRITE]] into an [[AND #imm]] so
  the sprite flickers with the frame counter.
\item When the countdown reaches zero, the routine switches into a
  wait-for-start phase.  A software timer advances in [[$06]] and
  when it rolls over, the BCD lives counter [[ZP_LIVES_BCD]] is decremented.  If it goes negative the routine
  returns and the main-loop exit check at [[$7208]] takes over
  (game-over path).
\item While waiting, the routine reads the keyboard, the two input
  handler slots ([[ZP_INPUT_1]] / [[ZP_INPUT_2]]) and the auto-start
  timeout counter [[$19]]; if any of those trip, the gameplay is
  activated: all entity-active slots in [[$8D]] are cleared, the
  main-loop input and sprite-render slots are restored to [[JSR]]
  opcodes, and [[$1E]] is set to [[$01]].  Otherwise a prompt sprite
  is drawn at a frame-dependent Y using sprite-table entry 1
  ([[SPRITE_TABLE_LO+1]] / [[SPRITE_TABLE_HI+1]]).
\end{itemize}

The routine also patches two ZP-aliased self-modifying operands in the
preceding game-engine chunks: the sprite-height immediate at
[[SMC_SR_HEIGHT]] ([[$64F6]], inside [[DRAW_PLAYER]]) and the Y-source
ZP operand at [[SMC_SR_YSRC]] ([[$64FA]], same routine).  On init it
re-points [[DRAW_PLAYER]] at the intro row in [[ZP_INTRO_Y]]; on
activation it restores the default $06 source and resets the
height immediate to [[$13]].

<<level intro defines>>=

; --- Zero-page (level-intro state) ---
ZP_INTRO_Y        = $17         ; Intro sprite Y row (also DRAW_PLAYER source during intro)
ZP_INTRO_COUNTDOWN = $18        ; Intro countdown frames remaining (starts at $12)
ZP_INTRO_TIMEOUT  = $19         ; Auto-start timeout counter (wraps through ZP_PAGE_FLAG to trigger)

; --- Level-data table consumed by the intro tick ---
LEVEL_DATA_BASE = $0200         ; Level data (ticks indexed 0..$12 via ZP_INTRO_COUNTDOWN)

; --- Main sprite pointer table (populated at runtime, indexed by sprite id) ---
SPRITE_TABLE_LO = $B000         ; Low bytes of sprite pointers ($B000-$B07F)
SPRITE_TABLE_HI = $B080         ; High bytes of sprite pointers ($B080-$B0FF)

; SMC_SR_HEIGHT / SMC_SR_YSRC are the self-modifying
; operand bytes inside DRAW_PLAYER; they are declared in the draw-player
; defines chunk.  LEVEL_INTRO_TICK patches them on init (to shrink the
; sprite and re-point it at ZP_INTRO_Y) and on activation (to restore
; the default $13 height and $06 Y source).

; --- Self-modifying operand slot inside DRAW_SPRITE ---
; SMC_SPRITE_MASK_OP / SMC_SPRITE_MASK_ARG are declared
; inline in the DRAW_SPRITE chunk as "= *" / "= *+1" over a DC.B $24 $00
; pair (disk-image encoding of BIT ZP_PAGE_FLAG, a 2-byte NOP in the normal draw
; path).  LEVEL_INTRO_TICK patches them to AND #<flicker> during the
; countdown to flash the sprite, then restores the BIT opcode.

@

<<level intro tick>>=

        ORG $699C
LEVEL_INTRO_TICK:
        SUBROUTINE
        ; Per-frame state machine for the level-start intro: countdown
        ; animation, tone pulses, wait-for-start, and activation.
        ;
        ; Inputs:
        ;   $1E                       --- state word
        ;                               $FF = needs init, $00 = intro running,
        ;                               $01 = gameplay active (fast RTS).
        ;   ZP_INTRO_COUNTDOWN  --- countdown frames remaining.
        ;   ZP_INTRO_TIMEOUT    --- auto-start timeout.
        ;   ZP_INTRO_Y          --- saved intro sprite Y row.
        ;   $FD                       --- frame counter (flicker / parity).
        ;   ZP_LIVES_BCD        --- BCD lives counter (goes negative = game over).
        ;   ZP_PLAYER_COL       --- saved on init; software timer
        ;                               during wait phase.
        ;   $02, $05, $0A..$0E, $1D, $8C --- game-state scratch cleared
        ;                               or seeded on init/activation.
        ;   $41                       --- entity-slot count (cleared on wait).
        ;   $83,X ($84 with X=1)      --- per-level initial Y column.
        ;   ZP_INPUT_1 / ZP_INPUT_2 --- handler pointers
        ;                               whose MSB can trigger activation.
        ;   LEVEL_DATA_BASE,$18       --- tone amplitude for countdown step.
        ;   SPRITE_TABLE_LO+1 /
        ;   SPRITE_TABLE_HI+1         --- "ready" prompt sprite (id 1).
        ;
        ; Behavior:
        ;   $1E > 0: RTS (fast path during gameplay).
        ;   $1E < 0: one-shot init --- disable input / movement / render
        ;     SMC slots; clear state; save $06 into ZP_INTRO_Y; point
        ;     DRAW_PLAYER at ZP_INTRO_Y (SMC_SR_YSRC); set
        ;     ZP_INTRO_COUNTDOWN=$12, ZP_INTRO_TIMEOUT=$40; $1E=0.
        ;     Falls through into the tick phase.
        ;   Tick phase (while ZP_INTRO_COUNTDOWN > 0): on odd frames
        ;     decrement the counter, decrement SMC_SR_HEIGHT and bump
        ;     ZP_INTRO_Y (unless $02 suppresses).  Patch the sprite
        ;     mask SMC to AND #<FD|$80> for flicker, draw the sprite
        ;     via DRAW_PLAYER, restore BIT opcode, then pulse
        ;     SFX_TONE with the level-data byte at LEVEL_DATA_BASE,$18.
        ;   Wait phase (ZP_INTRO_COUNTDOWN == 0): software timer in
        ;     $06 BCD-decrements ZP_LIVES_BCD when it wraps.  If
        ;     ZP_LIVES_BCD goes negative, RTS (game-over path).
        ;     Otherwise clear entity-active table ENTITY_HIT_STATE..$8D+$41,
        ;     poll keyboard / input-handler MSBs / timeout; on trigger
        ;     activate (set $1E=1, restore main-loop JSR slots, reset
        ;     SMC_SR_YSRC=$06, SMC_SR_HEIGHT=$13).  Otherwise draw the
        ;     "ready" prompt sprite (sprite-table id 1) at a row
        ;     that dips by 2 on every other frame once $19 >= $F0.
        ;
        ; Modifies:
        ;   $1E, $17, $18, $19, $02, $04, $05, $06, $0A, $0B, $0C,
        ;   $0D, $0E, $1D, $8C, $8D..$8D+$41 (entity-active table),
        ;   ZP_LIVES_BCD ($5E, BCD decrement),
        ;   SMC slots in MAIN_LOOP: SMC_INPUT, SMC_ASCEND
        ;, SMC_DESCEND, SMC_MOVE_LEFT,
        ;   SMC_MOVE_RIGHT, SMC_RENDER,
        ;   SMC_SR_HEIGHT, SMC_SR_YSRC,
        ;   SMC_SPRITE_MASK_OP, SMC_SPRITE_MASK_ARG,
        ;   SPRITE_PTR_LO, SPRITE_PTR_HI,
        ;   sprite-draw params ZP_SPRITE_W/H/Y/X, $5B, $5D, $56, $57.
        ; Clobbers: A, X, Y

; --- Fast path: gameplay active ---
        LDA $1E                         ; State word
        BMI .init                       ;   $FF = needs init
        BEQ .tick                       ;   $00 = intro running
        RTS                             ;   else (> 0) gameplay --- return

; --- One-shot initialisation ---
.init:
        LDA #$FF
        STA $0E                         ; Arm state byte
        LDA #$2C                        ; BIT opcode
        STA SMC_INPUT                   ; Disable input dispatch slot
        STA SMC_ASCEND                  ; Disable ascend slot
        STA SMC_DESCEND                 ; Disable descend slot
        STA SMC_MOVE_LEFT               ; Disable left slot
        STA SMC_MOVE_RIGHT              ; Disable right slot
        STA SMC_RENDER                  ; Disable sprite render slot
        LDA ZP_PLAYER_COL               ; Save current player column
        STA ZP_INTRO_Y                  ;   into intro Y
        LDA #$17
        STA SMC_SR_YSRC                 ; Re-point DRAW_PLAYER at ZP_INTRO_Y
        LDA #$00
        STA $05                         ; Clear scratch
        STA $1E                         ; State $00 = intro running
        STA ZP_MOVE_DIR                 ; Clear player horizontal move direction
        STA $0C                         ; Clear scratch
        LDA #$D0
        STA ZP_PLAYER_COL               ; Seed player column
        STA $8C                         ; Seed paired state byte
        LDA #$40
        STA ZP_INTRO_TIMEOUT            ; $40 frames before auto-start
        LDA #$12
        STA ZP_INTRO_COUNTDOWN          ; 18 countdown frames
;       fall through into .tick

; --- Countdown / wait dispatch ---
.tick:
        LDX ZP_INTRO_COUNTDOWN
        BEQ .wait                       ; Countdown done --- wait-for-start
        LDA $FD
        AND #$01
        BEQ .flicker_draw               ; Even frame: only draw
        DEX
        STX ZP_INTRO_COUNTDOWN          ; Odd frame: decrement counter
        LDA $02                         ; Suppress row bump?
        BNE .flicker_draw
        DEC SMC_SR_HEIGHT               ; Shrink DRAW_PLAYER sprite height
        INC ZP_INTRO_Y                  ;   and nudge Y down one row
.flicker_draw:
; --- Draw flickering intro sprite via DRAW_PLAYER ---
        LDA #$29                        ; AND #imm opcode
        STA SMC_SPRITE_MASK_OP          ;   patched into DRAW_SPRITE BIT slot
        LDA $FD
        ORA #$80                        ; Force bit 7 of flicker mask
        STA SMC_SPRITE_MASK_ARG
        JSR DRAW_PLAYER                 ; Draw the intro sprite
        LDA #$24                        ; BIT zp opcode
        STA SMC_SPRITE_MASK_OP          ; Restore DRAW_SPRITE BIT slot
        LDY ZP_INTRO_COUNTDOWN
        LDA LEVEL_DATA_BASE,Y           ; Tone amplitude for this tick
        LDX #$0A
        JSR SFX_TONE                    ; Pulse the speaker / delay
        RTS

; --- Wait-for-start phase: BCD-decrement level timer ---
.wait:
        LDA ZP_PLAYER_COL
        BEQ .check_level                ; $06 == 0: skip timer roll
        INC ZP_PLAYER_COL
        BNE .done                       ; No rollover --- just return
        BIT KBDSTROBE                   ; Rollover: clear keystrobe
        SED
        SEC
        LDA ZP_LIVES_BCD
        SBC #$01
        STA ZP_LIVES_BCD                ; BCD decrement of on-screen lives
        CLD
.done:
        RTS

; --- Check lives counter, then wait for input or timeout ---
.check_level:
        LDA ZP_LIVES_BCD
        BPL .wait_input                 ; Positive: lives remaining --- keep waiting
        RTS                             ; Negative: game-over path

.wait_input:
        LDX #$01
        STX $0E
        STX $0A
        LDA $83,X                       ; $84 --- per-level intro Y seed
        STA ZP_INTRO_Y
        LDA #$00
        STA $02                         ; Clear action flag
        LDA #$FF
        STA $1D
        LDX $41                         ; Entity-slot count
.clear_entities:
        STA $8D,X                       ; Mark slot inactive
        DEX
        BPL .clear_entities
        LDA #$06
        STA $03
        LDA #$00
        STA $01
        LDA KEYBOARD
        BMI .activate                   ; Key pressed --- start game
        LDY #$00
        LDA (ZP_INPUT_1),Y
        BMI .activate                   ; Input handler 1 asserts start
        LDA (ZP_INPUT_2),Y
        BMI .activate                   ; Input handler 2 asserts start
        INC ZP_INTRO_TIMEOUT
        BEQ .activate                   ; Timeout overflow --- auto-start

; --- Draw "ready" prompt sprite while waiting ---
        LDA ZP_INTRO_TIMEOUT
        CMP #$F0
        BCC .prompt_draw
        LDA $FD
        AND #$01
        BEQ .prompt_draw
        LDA ZP_INTRO_Y
        SEC
        SBC #$02
        STA ZP_SPRITE_Y                 ; Dip two rows on alternating late frames
        JMP .prompt_params
.prompt_draw:
        LDA ZP_INTRO_Y
        STA ZP_SPRITE_Y
.prompt_params:
        LDA #$03
        STA ZP_SPRITE_W
        LDA #$0F
        STA ZP_SPRITE_H
        LDA #$14
        STA ZP_SPRITE_X                 ; X column 20
        LDA SPRITE_TABLE_LO+1           ; Sprite id 1 --- low
        STA SPRITE_PTR_LO
        LDA SPRITE_TABLE_HI+1           ; Sprite id 1 --- high
        STA SPRITE_PTR_HI
        JSR DRAW_SPRITE
        RTS

; --- Activation: restore main-loop slots and flip state to "running" ---
; The tail of this block (from RESUME_GAMEPLAY_SMC onward) is a second
; entry point jumped to by GAME_START_INIT --- the 13-byte SMC-patch
; that re-enables input and sprite rendering in MAIN_LOOP.  The prefix
; ($6A95..$6AA6) reseeds player column + gameplay-active flags and is
; only reached by falling through from the wait-for-start branch above.
.activate:
        LDA ZP_INTRO_Y
        STA ZP_PLAYER_COL               ; Restore player column
        LDA $0A
        STA $09
        STA $0C
        STA $0B                         ; Seed $09, $0B, $0C from ZP_PLAYER_FLOOR
        LDA #$01
        STA $1E                         ; State = gameplay active
        STA $0D
RESUME_GAMEPLAY_SMC:
        ; Sub-entry: re-patch MAIN_LOOP's SMC slots to enable input
        ; dispatch and sprite rendering.  Called via [[JMP]] from
        ; GAME_START_INIT when starting (or restarting) a game.
        LDA #$06
        STA SMC_SR_YSRC                 ; DRAW_PLAYER reads ZP_PLAYER_COL again
        LDA #$20                        ; JSR opcode
        STA SMC_INPUT                   ; Re-enable input dispatch
        STA SMC_RENDER                  ; Re-enable sprite render
        LDA #$13
        STA SMC_SR_HEIGHT               ; Restore default sprite height
        RTS
@ %def LEVEL_INTRO_TICK RESUME_GAMEPLAY_SMC

\section{Special sprite: per-frame tick}

[[SPECIAL_TICK]] at [[$6ABA]] is the tick routine for the ``special''
sprite slot drawn by [[DRAW_ENTITIES]] phase~3 (see the
entity-draw-dispatcher section above).  It pairs with [[SPECIAL_DRAW]] at
[[$6B39]] the same way the three enemy slots pair their
\texttt{advance}/\texttt{draw} routines.  Both are called
unconditionally from [[MAIN_LOOP]], immediately after the HUD tile
update.

\paragraph{What the slot represents.}  The ``special'' sprite is a
bonus creature that walks horizontally across the playfield, colliding
with (and killing) floor-enemies in the four-slot [[$9B]] table that
[[ENEMY_C_DRAW]] and the beam subsystem target.  After four kills the
creature explodes into a fall/drift animation handled by the
[[SPECIAL_DRAW]] companion.  If the player's sprite overlaps the
drifting puff, the score is awarded [[$0500]] BCD via [[SCORE_ADD]] ---  % TODO-SYM: $0500
five hundred points, the classic arcade ``catch a bonus'' payoff ---
and the slot returns to its inactive countdown.

\paragraph{Slot state machine.}  [[ZP_SPECIAL_STATE]] is the
one-byte state:

\begin{itemize}
\item [[$00]] --- inactive: an 8-bit timer in [[ZP_SPECIAL_POS]] is
  incremented each frame, and its wrap ($0\to1$ roll-over of the low
  byte) reseeds the slot by falling into the \emph{rearm} block at
  [[$6B14]].
\item [[$01]] (any positive value) --- active: advance the 16-bit
  position [[ZP_SPECIAL_POS]] by [[$0002]] per frame, and
  once it reaches [[$035A]] rearm the slot.  Set by the rearm block.  % TODO-SYM: $035A
\item [[$FF]] (any negative value) --- drift: the sprite is  % TODO-SYM: $FF
  falling/climbing after a 4-kill defeat; row [[$AE]] is moved down by 2
  per frame, but at the four ``ladder'' rows ([[$34]], [[$5C]], [[$84]], [[$AC]])
  \mbox{94\,\%} of frames return early with no motion and the
  remaining \mbox{$\sim$6\,\%} (gated on [[ZP_PRNG_A]] [[$5F]] $<$ [[$0F]])
  move the sprite \emph{up} by 2 rows before advancing~X.  Set by
  [[SPECIAL_DRAW]]'s collision handler after the fourth floor-enemy
  kill; cleared by the player-catch path inside [[SPECIAL_DRAW]] when
  the puff is collected.
\end{itemize}

\paragraph{Sound slot.}  [[ZP_SPECIAL_SND_CTR]] is a
twelve-step ascending-tone counter that plays one click per frame
through [[SND_DELAY_UP]] ([[$109E]], duration~[[$0A]]) as it decrements
from~[[$0B]] down to~[[$00]], then idles at [[$FF]] (negative $\Rightarrow$  % TODO-SYM: $FF
skip).  The pitch bytes live in the page-2 table
[[SND_PITCH_TBL_SPECIAL]] ([[$0218]], 12 entries).  The counter is armed
to~[[$06]] by [[SPECIAL_DRAW]] on the four-kill defeat edge --- a short
descending ``defeat jingle'' --- but is \emph{not} rearmed on the
normal per-cycle rearm at [[$6B14]], which is silent.  Cold start leaves
[[$B5]] at its zero-page residual; the BMI gate keeps the first
invocations silent until [[SPECIAL_DRAW]] arms it.

\paragraph{Rearm block ([[$6B14]]).}  Reached from the inactive-timer
wrap (\texttt{INC [[$AC]] $\Rightarrow$ 0}) and from the end-of-transit
edge ([[$AC]] hits [[$5A]] with [[$AD]]=[[$03]]).  Resets [[ZP_SPECIAL_POS]] to
[[$003E]] (just past the rearm threshold so the next frame starts a fresh  % TODO-SYM: $003E
traversal), picks a floor-row anchor from
[[ENEMY_C_ROW_TBL]]$[\hbox{PRNG}\bmod 4]$ (one of the three defined
entries at [[$85]]/[[$86]]/[[$87]]; index 0 reads the [[$84]] base byte which is  % TODO-SYM: $85 $86 $87
the same shared table as the enemy-C row reload), subtracts [[$0B]] to
place the sprite above the floor, arms [[ZP_SPECIAL_HP]] to~4
``hit points'' (the number of floor-enemies the sprite will kill
before exploding), and writes [[$01]] to [[ZP_SPECIAL_STATE]].

\paragraph{Why this was called ``SOUND\_UPDATE''.}  The previous EQU
stub name came from the prominent \texttt{JSR SND\_DELAY\_UP} at
[[$6AC3]].  In fact every per-frame entity tick in Drol emits a  % TODO-SYM: $6AC3
speaker-click via one of the three sound routines
([[SFX_TONE]]/[[SND_DELAY_DOWN]]/[[SND_DELAY_UP]]), and the tone here
is one of four simultaneous channels, not a dedicated sound
subsystem.  Renaming to [[SPECIAL_TICK]] aligns with the three other
``tick'' routines ([[ENEMY_A_ADVANCE]], [[ENEMY_B_ADVANCE]],
[[ENEMY_C_ADVANCE]]) and exposes the drift/rearm state machine that
was hidden by the old name.

<<special tick defines>>=

; --- Zero-page (special sprite slot) ---
; ZP_SPECIAL_STATE is the same byte aliased as ZP_SPECIAL_A in the
; draw-entities defines chunk.  Keep both names: the tick uses the
; state-machine reading, the draw uses the phase-3 activity gate.
ZP_SPECIAL_STATE = $AB          ; $00 inactive / positive active / negative drift
ZP_SPECIAL_POS   = $AC          ; 16-bit position; aliases ZP_SPECIAL_X/Y
; ZP_SPECIAL_ROW = $AE is declared in draw-entities defines (phase 3).
ZP_SPECIAL_SND_CTR = $B5        ; 12-step ascending-tone counter ($FF = idle)
ZP_SPECIAL_HP    = $08          ; Remaining floor-enemies to kill before defeat

; --- Page-2 sound pitch table ---
SND_PITCH_TBL_SPECIAL = $0218   ; 12 pitch bytes indexed by ZP_SPECIAL_SND_CTR
@

<<special tick>>=

        ORG $6ABA
SPECIAL_TICK:
        SUBROUTINE
        ; Per-frame tick for the ``special'' bonus-creature slot drawn
        ; by DRAW_ENTITIES phase 3 (cf. SPECIAL_DRAW).  Emits
        ; one ascending-tone click, then dispatches on state:
        ; inactive, active (advance X), or drift (fall with ladder
        ; pauses).  On transit end, falls into the rearm sub-entry.
        ;
        ; Inputs:
        ;   ZP_SPECIAL_SND_CTR  --- click-pitch index (BMI = idle).
        ;   ZP_SPECIAL_STATE    --- $00 inactive / +active / -drift.
        ;   ZP_SPECIAL_POS      --- 16-bit horizontal position.
        ;   ZP_SPECIAL_ROW      --- screen row (drift path only).
        ;   ZP_PRNG_A           --- 6%/94% split at drift-mode ladder
        ;                           rows; also reseed row anchor index
        ;                           on rearm.
        ;   ENEMY_C_ROW_TBL     --- 4-entry row table ENEMY_C_ROW_TBL..$87 (same
        ;                           shared table enemy-C reloads from).
        ;
        ; Behavior:
        ;   1. Emit a click from SND_PITCH_TBL_SPECIAL[$B5] via
        ;      SND_DELAY_UP (duration $0A); skip when the counter is
        ;      negative.
        ;   2. State dispatch:
        ;      $00: jump to inactive-timer block at $6B32.
        ;      -  : drift path --- at ladder rows ZP_DIFF_THRESH_A/ZP_DIFF_TMP/$84/$AC the
        ;           PRNG gates a $-$2 row move (6%) vs. RTS (94%);
        ;           otherwise $+$2 row and fall into the X-advance.
        ;      +  : active path --- advance only (no row change).
        ;   3. X-advance: add $0002 to ZP_SPECIAL_POS/ZP_SPECIAL_Y.  If $AC $>=$ $5A and
        ;      $AD $=$ $03, fall into the rearm block; else RTS.
        ;   4. Rearm: reset $AC/$AD to $003E, pick a row
        ;      anchor from ENEMY_C_ROW_TBL,[PRNG&3] minus $0B, arm HP to 4, set
        ;      state to ZP_LAST_DIR, RTS.
        ;
        ; Modifies:
        ;   ZP_SPECIAL_SND_CTR, ZP_SPECIAL_POS, ZP_SPECIAL_ROW,
        ;   ZP_SPECIAL_HP, ZP_SPECIAL_STATE, ZP_PRNG_A (via PRNG).
        ; Clobbers: A, X, Y

; --- Emit ascending-tone click ---
        LDX ZP_SPECIAL_SND_CTR
        BMI .after_click                ; Negative = idle
        LDA SND_PITCH_TBL_SPECIAL,X     ; Pitch byte
        LDX #$0A                        ; Duration = 10 clicks
        JSR SND_DELAY_UP                ; Ascending tone
        DEC ZP_SPECIAL_SND_CTR
.after_click:

; --- State dispatch ---
        LDA ZP_SPECIAL_STATE
        BEQ .inactive_hop               ; $00 = inactive -> timer jump
        BMI .drift                      ; $80+ = drift/dying
        BPL .advance                    ; $01..$7F = active
.inactive_hop:
        JMP .inactive_timer             ; (out-of-reach relative branch)

; --- Drift: fall with ladder-row pauses ---
.drift:
        LDA ZP_SPECIAL_ROW              ; $AE
        CMP #$34
        BEQ .at_ladder
        CMP #$5C
        BEQ .at_ladder
        CMP #$84
        BEQ .at_ladder
        CMP #$AC
        BEQ .at_ladder
        CLC
        ADC #$02                        ; Not at ladder: row += 2 (fall)
        STA ZP_SPECIAL_ROW
        JMP .advance
.at_ladder:
        LDA ZP_PRNG_A
        CMP #$0F
        BCS .exit                       ; ~94%: stay put at ladder
        LDA ZP_SPECIAL_ROW
        SEC
        SBC #$02                        ; ~6%: climb up one rung
        STA ZP_SPECIAL_ROW

; --- Advance 16-bit X position by ZP_ACTION_DIR ---
.advance:
        LDA ZP_SPECIAL_POS
        CLC
        ADC #$02
        STA ZP_SPECIAL_POS
        LDA ZP_SPECIAL_POS+1
        ADC #$00
        STA ZP_SPECIAL_POS+1
        LDA ZP_SPECIAL_POS
        CMP #$5A
        BCS .check_end                  ; Low >= $5A: maybe end of transit
.exit:
        RTS
.check_end:
        LDA ZP_SPECIAL_POS+1
        CMP #$03
        BNE .exit                       ; High != 3: keep going

; --- Rearm slot (entered via fall-through or JMP from timer wrap) ---
SPECIAL_REARM:
        LDA #$3E
        STA ZP_SPECIAL_POS              ; Reset position to $003E
        LDA #$00
        STA ZP_SPECIAL_POS+1
        JSR PRNG                        ; Random row-anchor index
        AND #$03
        TAX
        LDA ENEMY_C_ROW_TBL,X           ; $84/$85/$86/$87
        SEC
        SBC #$0B                        ; Rise above floor
        STA ZP_SPECIAL_ROW
        LDA #$04
        STA ZP_SPECIAL_HP               ; 4 HP (kills before defeat)
        LDA #$01
        STA ZP_SPECIAL_STATE            ; Activate
.rearm_rts:
        RTS

; --- Inactive timer: increment $AC; wrap triggers rearm ---
; Reuses .rearm_rts above as its not-yet-wrapped return.
.inactive_timer:
        INC ZP_SPECIAL_POS
        BNE .rearm_rts                  ; Not yet wrapped: return
        JMP SPECIAL_REARM               ; Wrap: rearm slot
@ %def SPECIAL_TICK SPECIAL_REARM ZP_SPECIAL_STATE ZP_SPECIAL_POS ZP_SPECIAL_SND_CTR ZP_SPECIAL_HP SND_PITCH_TBL_SPECIAL

\section{Special sprite: per-frame draw}

[[SPECIAL_DRAW]] at [[$6B39]] is the direct draw partner of
[[SPECIAL_TICK]].  Both are invoked unconditionally from [[MAIN_LOOP]]
each frame; [[SPECIAL_TICK]] updates the slot's timer/state and
[[SPECIAL_DRAW]] renders the sprite and handles both of its collision
tests (four-kill body-collision with the floor-enemy table, and the
drift-puff player-catch).

\paragraph{Three visual phases.}  The routine gates on
[[ZP_SPECIAL_STATE]] just like the tick:

\begin{itemize}
\item [[$00]] (\textbf{inactive}) --- fall through to [[SPECIAL_INACTIVE_DRAW]]
  at [[$6CDB]], a 29-byte helper that draws a small [[$02]]$\times$[[$06]] marker
  sprite from the level-data pointer pair at [[$755B]]/[[$765B]] at a
  fixed screen position derived from the slot's row anchor ([[$AE]]).
  Conceptually the ``peek'' of the creature waiting off-screen.
\item positive (\textbf{active}) --- perspective-transform the 16-bit
  position [[ZP_SPECIAL_POS]] against the player's world-X, draw a
  [[$06]]$\times$[[$14]] body sprite, and run a hit test against the  % TODO-SYM: $14
  four-slot floor-enemy table at [[$9B]]/[[$9F]]/[[$A3]] (the same slots
  targeted by [[ENEMY_C_DRAW]] and the beam subsystem).  On a floor-enemy
  overlap: clear that slot ($[[$00]] \to [[$9B]][X]$), decrement
  [[ZP_SPECIAL_HP]], and on the fourth kill (HP $=0$) set
  drift mode and arm the defeat-jingle sound counter.
\item negative (\textbf{drift}) --- draw a [[$04]]$\times$[[$0F]] puff
  sprite from the per-perspective-frame pointer table
  [[SPECIAL_PUFF_LO]]/[[SPECIAL_PUFF_HI]] ([[$AFDA]]/[[$B05A]], indexed by
  the same perspective-frame-index Y the body path uses), then test
  whether the player's sprite overlaps the puff.  On a catch: award
  [[$0500]] BCD via [[SCORE_ADD]], clear [[ZP_SPECIAL_STATE]], arm  % TODO-SYM: $0500
  [[ZP_SPECIAL_SND_CTR_B]] to~4 for a short catch tone, and
  bump the position so the slot immediately falls into its inactive
  countdown.
\end{itemize}

\paragraph{SMC-chained walk-cycle body draw.}  Unlike the three enemy
slots --- which index a per-frame sprite table directly from
[[ZP_FRAME_COUNTER]] bits --- [[SPECIAL_DRAW]]'s body path uses a
\emph{self-modifying dispatch}: a [[JMP]] at [[$6BE8]] whose operand bytes  % TODO-SYM: $6BE8
[[SMC_SPECIAL_BODY_LO]]/[[SMC_SPECIAL_BODY_HI]] point
to one of six small handlers at [[$6C3F]]--[[$6CC0]].  Each handler rewrites  % TODO-SYM: $6CC0
the operand bytes to the \emph{next} handler in a ring, then patches
[[SMC_DS_SRC_LO]]/[[SMC_DS_SRC_HI]] with its own sprite source pointer
and calls [[DRAW_SPRITE]].  The six handlers select from a four-entry
per-level sprite-pointer table at [[$7578]]/[[$7678]]--[[$758D]]/[[$768D]] using
offsets $\{0, 7, 14, 21, 14, 7\}$ --- a \emph{palindromic} walk cycle
(poses 0, 1, 2, 3, 2, 1) that gives the creature a bidirectional
walk-in-place look without storing a frame index in RAM.  The initial
operand [[$6C3F]] on disk starts the cycle at handler~1.

\paragraph{Which [[DRAW_SPRITE]] variant.}  All four sub-draws
([[SPECIAL_INACTIVE_DRAW]], the six body steps, the drift-puff, and
the defeat transition) call [[DRAW_SPRITE]] at [[$656F]] --- not
[[DRAW_SPRITE_PLAYFIELD]] at [[$65D5]].  This is the same transparent-OR
blit used by the three enemy slots (and distinct from the playfield
blit used by [[DRAW_ENTITIES]]).  SMC source pointers go to
[[SMC_DS_SRC_LO]]/[[SMC_DS_SRC_HI]], the
[[DRAW_SPRITE]] operand bytes, not the playfield variant.

\paragraph{Sound slot.}  [[SPECIAL_DRAW]] drives a \emph{second} sound
counter [[ZP_SPECIAL_SND_CTR_B]] with a companion pitch table
[[SND_PITCH_TBL_SPECIAL_B]] at [[$021F]].  Unlike the ascending-tone
counter the tick uses, this one clicks through [[SFX_TONE]] at
duration [[$08]] --- a shorter, higher click.  It is armed to~[[$04]] on
the player-catches-puff edge, producing a four-click ``pickup'' tone.
[[$B6]] also idles at negative (BMI skips the click).

\paragraph{Player-overlap boxes.}

\begin{itemize}
\item \textbf{Body-phase catch at [[$6BCA]]} (fires on the same frame as  % TODO-SYM: $6BCA
  the fourth-kill defeat, i.e.\ when the creature explodes under the
  player): X-box [[[$40]], [[$56]]) on the transformed screen-X
  [[$AF]]; Y-box [[$06-$13, $06+$12]] on [[$AE]].  Wins set the
  hit-flag [[$1E]] = [[$FF]].  % TODO-SYM: $FF
\item \textbf{Drift-phase catch at [[$6C02]]}: X-box [[[$40]], [[$53]]), Y-box  % TODO-SYM: $6C02 $53
  [[$06-$0E, $06+$12]] on [[$AE]].  Wins award +[[$0500]] BCD and reset  % TODO-SYM: $0500
  the slot.
\end{itemize}

\paragraph{Perspective transform} (same shape as the enemy draws).
[[ZP_PLAYER_Y]] indexes
[[PERSPECTIVE_XOFF_LO]]/[[PERSPECTIVE_XOFF_HI]] minus
[[ZP_SPRITE_XREF]] to produce the player's world-X; subtracting
that from the creature's 16-bit [[ZP_SPECIAL_POS]] yields the
transformed screen-X in [[$AF]].  An off-screen test (high byte $\ne 0$
or low byte $\ge [[$A0]]$) short-circuits the draw with an RTS.  [[$AF]]
is then used as the index into [[PROJ_SCREEN_COL]] ([[$1C34]], the
horizontal-to-screen-column table) and [[PROJ_FRAME_IDX]] ([[$1B8F]],
horizontal-to-sprite-frame-index).

\paragraph{Why the previous ``ANIM\_UPDATE'' stub was wrong.}  The old
name described a superficial reading: the SMC-chained dispatch writes
bytes during execution, which resembles an animation update.  In fact
the SMC is an optimisation for a single sprite-slot \emph{draw} ---
the routine is the draw partner of [[SPECIAL_TICK]], emitting the
sprite, running two collision tests, awarding score, and managing the
defeat/catch state transitions.

\paragraph{Body-sprite art.}  Figure~\ref{fig:special_body_sprites}
shows all 28 body frames: four poses (the palindromic ring visits
them in order \{0,\,1,\,2,\,3,\,2,\,1\}) across seven perspective
depths.  Each body sprite is $[[$07]]\times[[$14]]$ in bytes  % TODO-SYM: $14
([[ZP_SPRITE_W]]~=~[[$06]], [[ZP_SPRITE_H]]~=~[[$14]]).  The drift-mode  % TODO-SYM: $14
puff set is shown in Figure~\ref{fig:special_puff_sprites}, and the
single $[[$03]]\times[[$06]]$ ``peek'' marker drawn during the inactive
countdown is included in Figure~\ref{fig:enemy_c_auxiliary} above.
All special-slot sprites live in the swappable level-data region
([[$8CBF]] for the peek through [[$9D00]]+ for the body poses) and were  % TODO-SYM: $8CBF $9D00
extracted from [[drol.dsk]] phase~0.

